奥本海默博士
Dr. Oppenheimer.

39
00:01:21,780 --> 00:01:23,190
奥本海默博士
Dr. Oppenheimer.

40
00:01:24,370 --> 00:01:28,240
在我们开始前  我相信你想要宣读一份声明
As we begin, I believe you have a statement to read into the record.

41
00:01:29,670 --> 00:01:31,040
是的  法官大人
Yes, your honor.

42
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:34,490
-我们不是法官  博士  -我明白
- We're not judges, Doctor. - No.

43
00:01:35,380 --> 00:01:36,660
你们当然不是
Of course.

44
00:01:41,970 --> 00:01:44,210
各位安全委员会的成员
Members of the security board,

45
00:01:44,970 --> 00:01:48,430
在你们对我的起诉书中提到的所谓审讯信息
the so-called interrogatory information in your indictment of me

46
00:01:48,430 --> 00:01:50,100
必须要结合我的工作与生活
cannot be fairly understood

47
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:54,140
才能被公正地理解
except in the context of my life, and my work.

48
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:56,430
他作证了多久
How long did he testify?

49
00:01:56,930 --> 00:01:59,180
说实话  我忘了
Honestly, I forget.

50
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:02,450
整个听证会进行了一个月
The whole hearing took a month.

51
00:02:02,450 --> 00:02:06,020
-简直是磨难  -我只读过文字记录
- An ordeal. - Oh, I've only read the transcripts.

52
00:02:08,410 --> 00:02:11,080
-谁会想为自己的一生辩护呢  -你当时不在吗
- Who'd want to justify their whole life? - You weren't there?

53
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:13,120
作为主席  我不能参加
As chairman, I wasn't allowed to be.

54
00:02:13,130 --> 00:02:15,490
他们真的会问这事吗
Are they really going to ask about it?

55
00:02:15,790 --> 00:02:17,210
这已经是很多年前了
It was years ago.

56
00:02:17,210 --> 00:02:19,080
-是四年前的事  -五年了
- Four years ago. - Five.

57
00:02:19,990 --> 00:02:21,670
奥本海默仍然让美国分裂
Oppenheimer still divides America.

58
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:23,960
委员会肯定会问起你当时的立场的
The committee's going to want to know where you stood.

59
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:28,280
瑟蒙德参议员让我转告你  不要觉得自己在受审
Senator Thurmond asked me to say not to feel that you're on trial.

60
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:31,730
说来有趣  我本来没觉得  直到你提起
Oh, funny. I didn't, until you just said that.

61
00:02:31,730 --> 00:02:33,440
-真的  施特劳斯先生  -是上将
- Really, Mr. Strauss... - It's Admiral.

62
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:36,690
上将  施特劳斯上将  这只是走个形式
Admiral. Admiral Strauss, this is a formality.

63
00:02:36,690 --> 00:02:38,690
艾森豪威尔总统已经邀请您加入他的内阁
President Eisenhower has asked you to be in his cabinet.

64
00:02:38,690 --> 00:02:40,690
参议院除了顺从他  别无选择
The Senate really has no choice but to confirm him.

65
00:02:40,690 --> 00:02:43,060
那如果他们提起奥本海默呢
And if they bring up Oppenheimer?

66
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:45,320
如果他们提起奥本海默  你就如实回答
When they bring up Oppenheimer, you answer honestly,

67
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:47,950
你履行了职责  这一点没有任何参议员能否认
no senator can deny you did your duty.

68
00:02:47,950 --> 00:02:49,900
只是会有点令人不适
It'll be uncomfortable.

69
00:02:50,330 --> 00:02:52,360
毕竟谁会想为自己的一生辩护呢
Who'd want to justify their whole life?

70
00:02:57,670 --> 00:02:59,620
你当初为什么离开美国
Why did you leave the United States?

71
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:05,430
我想去学最新的物理知识
I... I wanted to study the new physics.

72
00:03:05,430 --> 00:03:06,960
在这里不能学吗
Was there nowhere here?

73
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:11,130
伯克利不就有一流的理论物理系吗
I thought Berkeley had the leading theoretical physics department.

74
00:03:11,270 --> 00:03:13,800
是的  那是我创立的
Yes, once I built it.

75
00:03:13,940 --> 00:03:15,270
但在那之前我得先去欧洲
But first I had to go to Europe.

76
00:03:15,270 --> 00:03:18,520
我去了剑桥  师从帕特里克·布莱克特
I went to Cambridge, to study under Patrick Blackett.

77
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:20,970
比起在美国  你在那里是不是更开心
Were you happier there than in America?

78
00:03:21,610 --> 00:03:23,560
-更开心  -没错
- Happier? - Yes.

79
00:03:27,450 --> 00:03:28,570
不
No.

80
00:03:28,910 --> 00:03:30,530
不  我当时
No, I, uh...

81
00:03:32,950 --> 00:03:35,200
我当时很想家
I was homesick and...

82
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,990
情绪上也不成熟
emotionally immature...

83
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:44,870
总能看到某个隐藏的宇宙  因此深受困扰
Troubled by visions of a... hidden universe.

84
00:03:55,850 --> 00:03:57,590
我在实验室一无是处
Useless in the lab.

85
00:04:01,940 --> 00:04:03,980
天哪  奥本海默
Christ, Oppenheimer.

86
00:04:04,610 --> 00:04:06,350
你昨晚没睡吗
Have you had any sleep?

87
00:04:08,530 --> 00:04:09,860
重来
Start again.

88
00:04:09,990 --> 00:04:11,730
我得去听讲座  老师
I need to go to a lecture, sir.

89
00:04:12,370 --> 00:04:13,530
至于吗
Why?

90
00:04:13,910 --> 00:04:15,490
是尼尔斯·玻尔的讲座
It's Niels Bohr.

91
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:19,660
我忘得一干二净
I completely forgot.

92
00:04:20,210 --> 00:04:22,580
好了  咱们走
Alright! Let's go.

93
00:04:24,630 --> 00:04:26,340
不  你不能去  奥本海默
Oh no, not you, Oppenheimer.

94
00:04:26,340 --> 00:04:28,210
你镀完板子再走
You finish coating those plates.

95
00:05:08,180 --> 00:05:11,800
量子物理不是向前迈出的一步
Quantum physics is not a step forward.

96
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:15,810
而是一种理解现实的全新方式
It is a new way to understand reality.

97
00:05:15,810 --> 00:05:17,620
爱因斯坦打开了大门
Einstein's opened the door.

98
00:05:17,620 --> 00:05:21,650
让人得以窥视我们所生活的世界中的另一个世界
Now we are peering through, seeing a world inside our world,

99
00:05:21,650 --> 00:05:28,350
那里充斥着能量和悖论  并非所有人都能接受
a world of energy and paradox that not everyone can accept.

100
00:06:11,330 --> 00:06:12,400
你没事吧
You alright?

101
00:06:13,110 --> 00:06:15,870
尼尔斯  这位是J·罗伯特·奥本海默
Nils, meet J. Robert Oppenheimer.

102
00:06:15,870 --> 00:06:17,580
J代表什么
What's the J stand for?

103
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:18,950
没什么
Nothing, apparently.

104
00:06:18,950 --> 00:06:21,510
你去听了我的讲座  问了全场唯一一个好问题
You were at my lecture. You asked the only good question.

105
00:06:21,610 --> 00:06:23,070
没人否认他的洞察力
No one's denying his insight.

106
00:06:23,070 --> 00:06:26,200
但他的实验室工作还有一些不足
It's his laboratory work that leaves a little to be desired.

107
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:27,880
我听说你之前也是那样回答的
I heard you give the same answer...

108
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:30,420
在哈佛  没错  而你问了同样的问题
At Harvard, yes, and you asked the same question.

109
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:31,800
为什么又问一遍
Why ask again?

110
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,330
我不喜欢你之前的回答
I hadn't liked your answer.

111
00:06:34,550 --> 00:06:37,430
-那你对昨天的回答还满意吗  -很满意
- Did you like it better yesterday? - A lot.

112
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:41,890
即便没准备好应付石头下的蛇  你也可以抬起它
You can lift a stone without being ready for the snake that's revealed.

113
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:44,180
现在你似乎已经准备好了
Now it seems you're ready.

114
00:06:44,410 --> 00:06:46,390
但你在实验室并不开心
But you don't enjoy the lab.

115
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:49,570
所以离开剑桥吧  离开那些烧杯和药水
So get out of Cambridge, with its beakers and potions.

116
00:06:49,570 --> 00:06:52,230
去一个能让你思考的地方
Go somewhere they'll let you think.

117
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:54,310
是哪里呢
Where?

118
00:06:55,870 --> 00:06:57,530
-哥廷根  -玻恩
- Göttingen. - Born.

119
00:06:57,530 --> 00:06:58,620
玻恩
Born.

120
00:06:58,620 --> 00:07:03,290
去德国  跟着马克斯·玻恩学习理论物理
Get to Germany, study under Max Born, learn the ways of theory.

121
00:07:03,390 --> 00:07:04,820
我会跟他打招呼的
I'll send word.

122
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:06,780
有虫眼
Worm hole.

123
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,000
你的数学怎么样
How's your mathematics?

124
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,130
还没好到能支持他成为他想成为的物理学家
Not good enough for the physicist he wants to be.

125
00:07:12,130 --> 00:07:14,470
代数就像乐谱
Algebra's like sheet music,

126
00:07:14,470 --> 00:07:18,350
重要的不是你识不识谱  而是你能否听到音乐
the important thing isn't can you read music, it's can you hear it.

127
00:07:18,350 --> 00:07:21,050
你能听到音乐吗  罗伯特
Can you hear the music, Robert?

128
00:07:21,930 --> 00:07:23,220
是的  我能
Yes, I can.

129
00:08:59,490 --> 00:09:01,360
怀俄明州参议员
The senator from Wyoming.

130
00:09:01,950 --> 00:09:03,080
施特劳斯上将
Admiral Strauss,

131
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:06,410
我对您和J·罗伯特·奥本海默博士的关系很感兴趣
I'm interested in your relationship with Dr. J. Robert Oppenheimer.

132
00:09:06,410 --> 00:09:08,700
你们在1947年相识
You met him in 1947.

133
00:09:09,210 --> 00:09:10,370
是的
Correct.

134
00:09:10,630 --> 00:09:13,290
你当时是原子能委员会的委员
You were a commissioner of the Atomic Energy Commission.

135
00:09:13,290 --> 00:09:17,050
是的  但我与罗伯特认识时
I was, but I actually met Robert in my capacity

136
00:09:17,050 --> 00:09:20,750
我的身份是普林斯顿高等研究院的董事会成员
as board member of the Institute for Advanced Study at Princeton.

137
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:21,680
当时
It was...

138
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:25,100
正值战后  他已经是世界知名的伟大物理学家
after the war, he was world-renowned as the great man of physics,

139
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:29,310
我决心请他执掌研究院
and I was determined to get him to run the Institute.

140
00:09:39,030 --> 00:09:41,950
奥本海默博士  幸会
Dr. Oppenheimer. An honor.

141
00:09:41,950 --> 00:09:43,120
你好  施特拉斯先生
Mr. Strauss.

142
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:44,690
应该是"施特劳斯"
It's pronounced "Strauss".

143
00:09:45,410 --> 00:09:46,660
不管是"欧本海默"还是"奥本海默"
"Oppenheimer", "Oppenheimer"...

144
00:09:46,660 --> 00:09:49,240
随便怎么读  对方都知道我是犹太人
Either way you say it, they know I'm Jewish.

145
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:52,880
我是曼哈顿以马内利会堂的会长
I'm president of Temple Emanu-El in Manhattan.

146
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:55,630
叫"施特劳斯"只是遵从南方的发音习惯而已
"Strauss" is just a Southern pronunciation.

147
00:09:55,630 --> 00:09:59,630
总之  欢迎来到研究院  你在这应该会过得很开心
Anyway, welcome to the Institute. I think you'll be very happy here.

148
00:09:59,630 --> 00:10:01,550
这里的通勤也很方便
Yes, well, you'll love the commute.

149
00:10:01,550 --> 00:10:04,090
那栋房子就是为入职后的你准备的  你和你的妻子
The position comes with that house for you and your wife,

150
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:06,220
还有  两个孩子对吗
and your... is it two children?

151
00:10:06,220 --> 00:10:07,270
没错  两个孩子
Yes, two.

152
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:10,180
我很敬仰你的工作
I'm a great admirer of your work.

153
00:10:10,230 --> 00:10:12,690
你是科班出身的物理学家吗  施特劳斯先生
You're a physicist by training, Mr. Strauss?

154
00:10:12,690 --> 00:10:14,770
抱歉  这里是公共休息室  茶点时间是四点
I'm sorry, uh, common room, four o'clock tea.

155
00:10:14,770 --> 00:10:17,640
不  我没受过专业物理学训练
No, I'm not trained in physics or anything else.

156
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:18,610
我都是自学的
I'm a self-made man.

157
00:10:18,610 --> 00:10:20,770
可以理解
Ah, I can relate to that.

158
00:10:20,860 --> 00:10:23,360
-是吗  -我父亲也是
- Really? - Yes, my father was one.

159
00:10:24,620 --> 00:10:27,480
这里就是你的办公室
And this would be your office.

160
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:38,830
听说下午他一般都在那里
I'm told he's there in most afternoons.

161
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,550
其实我一直很好奇
You know, I've always wondered

162
00:10:40,550 --> 00:10:44,130
为什么你没有邀请他参加曼哈顿计划
why you didn't involve him in the Manhattan Project.

163
00:10:45,890 --> 00:10:48,170
毕竟他是我们这个时代最伟大的科学家
Greatest scientific mind of our time.

164
00:10:48,220 --> 00:10:49,710
是他那个时代
Of his time.

165
00:10:50,230 --> 00:10:52,390
爱因斯坦发表相对论
Einstein published his Theory of Relativity

166
00:10:52,390 --> 00:10:55,600
已经是40多年前的事了
more than 40 years ago now.

167
00:10:56,190 --> 00:10:58,820
但他永远无法接受它所揭示的量子世界
Could never embrace the quantum world it revealed.

168
00:10:58,820 --> 00:11:00,400
"上帝不会掷骰子"
"God doesn't play dice."

169
00:11:00,990 --> 00:11:02,350
没错
Precisely.

170
