00:29:12,780 --> 00:29:14,120
我不懂  你到底要我怎样
I don't understand what you want from me.

524
00:29:14,120 --> 00:29:16,030
我什么也不要
I don't want anything from you!

525
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:21,120
-说是这么说  却又打电话找我  -你别接啊
- Well, you say that, and then you call. - Well, don't answer.

526
00:29:21,910 --> 00:29:23,540
你打来我一定会接的
I'll always answer.

527
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:29,830
行吧
Fine.

528
00:29:30,180 --> 00:29:31,920
别再送花就行了
Just no more flowers.

529
00:29:33,250 --> 00:29:34,230
你不来吗
You're not coming?

530
00:29:36,490 --> 00:29:38,550
要知难而退啊  罗伯特
You have to know when you're beaten, Robert.

531
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:42,590
没那么简单  哈康
It's not that simple, Haak.

532
00:29:42,950 --> 00:29:46,170
薛瓦利埃  你好  芭芭拉  你好
Chevalier, good to see you. It's O...Barbara, good to see you.

533
00:29:46,170 --> 00:29:48,670
还有声名远扬的奥本海默博士
And the illustrious Dr. Oppenheimer.

534
00:29:48,840 --> 00:29:50,410
-我是埃尔滕顿  -幸会
- I'm Eltenton. - Oh, pleasure.

535
00:29:50,410 --> 00:29:51,370
请进
Please, please.

536
00:29:51,630 --> 00:29:54,790
大学里成立劳工组织的事  你来讲两句吧
Why don't you say a word about organized labor on campuses?

537
00:29:54,870 --> 00:29:57,180
好吗  请让一让  让一让
Yes? Coming through, coming through!

538
00:29:57,180 --> 00:29:58,250
我在壳牌工作
I work at Shell.

539
00:29:58,250 --> 00:30:00,630
化学家和工程师都加入了组织
We've signed up chemists, we've signed up engineers.

540
00:30:00,780 --> 00:30:02,750
科学界和学术界人士也一起吧
So why not sciences and academia?

541
00:30:02,850 --> 00:30:10,900
奥比  奥比  奥比  奥比
Oppie! Oppie! Oppie! Oppie!

542
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:18,510
讲师都加入了
Teachers are unionized.

543
00:30:18,910 --> 00:30:20,470
教授为什么不呢
Why not professors?

544
00:30:20,470 --> 00:30:21,710
你不是还有事吗
Don't you have somewhere to be?

545
00:30:21,710 --> 00:30:24,150
劳伦斯  科研人士也有权利
Lawrence, academics have rights too.

546
00:30:24,320 --> 00:30:26,540
我不是说那个  我有个组会要开
Look, it's not that. I've got a group coming.

547
00:30:27,380 --> 00:30:29,250
-那我旁听  -这次不行
- I'll sit in. - Not this one.

548
00:30:35,840 --> 00:30:37,750
理查德  布什博士
Richard, Dr. Bush.

549
00:30:37,750 --> 00:30:39,370
二位怎么北上来这里了
What brings you two up north?

550
00:30:48,830 --> 00:30:51,980
理查德  你转告露丝  我周四去帕萨迪纳
Richard, you tell Ruth I'll be down in Pasadena Thursday.

551
00:31:01,770 --> 00:31:03,870
黑洞的文章  中了
Paper on black holes, it's in!

552
00:31:05,610 --> 00:31:06,670
哈特兰在哪儿
Where's Hartland?

553
00:31:07,300 --> 00:31:09,420
找一下哈特兰  去找他
Get Hartland. Get Hartland.

554
00:31:09,520 --> 00:31:13,160
1939年9月1日  世界会铭记这一天
September 1st, 1939? The world's gonna remember this day.

555
00:31:14,700 --> 00:31:16,690
哈特兰  我们的论文刊印出来了
Oh, Hartland, our paper, it's in print.

556
00:31:16,700 --> 00:31:18,120
有人抢了你的风头
You've been upstaged.

557
00:31:22,410 --> 00:31:24,830
在不列颠战役期间  我发现
During the Battle of Britain, I found myself

558
00:31:25,330 --> 00:31:27,540
自己越来越难以认同
increasingly out of sympathy with the...

559
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:30,960
共产党人主张的中立政策
policy of neutrality that communists advocated.

560
00:31:30,960 --> 00:31:33,840
但希特勒入侵苏联后  我们与苏联成了盟友
But after Hitler invaded Russia and we became allies,

561
00:31:34,290 --> 00:31:36,520
你对共产党人的认同有没有回升
these communist sympathies, do they return?

562
00:31:36,610 --> 00:31:37,500
没有
No.

563
00:31:38,510 --> 00:31:40,370
我得声明一下
I need to make clear that

564
00:31:40,370 --> 00:31:43,050
我改变了对苏联的看法
my changing views on Russia did not mean

565
00:31:43,050 --> 00:31:45,880
并不意味着我会与其他持不同观点的人绝交
a sharp break from those who held different views.

566
00:31:46,180 --> 00:31:48,520
我妻子吉蒂在之前的一段婚姻中
For a year or two during a previous marriage,

567
00:31:48,520 --> 00:31:51,780
当过一两年共产党员
my wife Kitty had been a Communist Party member.

568
00:31:56,650 --> 00:31:57,930
我把好东西都藏在这里
This is where I keep the good stuff.

569
00:31:57,930 --> 00:31:59,780
这里不是托尔曼夫妇家吗
Well, I thought this was the Tolmans' house.

570
00:31:59,780 --> 00:32:01,920
我在加州理工的时候就住他们家
I live with them while I'm at Caltech.

571
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,480
你俩需要我帮忙吗
Do you two need anything?

572
00:32:03,540 --> 00:32:04,700
不用  露丝
We're good, Ruthie.

573
00:32:06,020 --> 00:32:08,970
话说  你是一名生物学家
So, you're a biologist.

574
00:32:09,280 --> 00:32:12,340
但我毕业之后就当了家庭主妇
Well, somehow I have graduated to housewife.

575
00:32:12,630 --> 00:32:14,970
你能给我讲讲量子力学吗
Can you explain quantum mechanics to me?

576
00:32:15,030 --> 00:32:17,780
-听起来挺玄乎的  -确实
- Seems baffling. - Yes, it is.

577
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:20,780
这个杯子
Well, this glass,

578
00:32:21,720 --> 00:32:24,990
杯中的酒  这个台面
this drink... this countertop...

579
00:32:26,190 --> 00:32:27,370
还有我们的身体
Our bodies.

580
00:32:29,190 --> 00:32:30,120
一切的一切
All of it.

581
00:32:31,430 --> 00:32:33,070
几乎都是空的
It's mostly empty space.

582
00:32:33,330 --> 00:32:36,560
是束缚在一起的一组组微小能量波
Groupings of tiny energy waves bound together.

583
00:32:36,560 --> 00:32:37,500
被什么束缚
By what?

584
00:32:37,760 --> 00:32:39,810
足够强的吸引力
Forces of attraction strong enough

585
00:32:39,810 --> 00:32:44,000
强到能让我们认为物质是固体
to convince us that matter is solid.

586
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:46,400
让我的身体不会穿过你的身体
Stop my body passing through yours.

587
00:32:58,690 --> 00:33:00,410
你跟哈里森博士是夫妻
You're married to Dr. Harrison.

588
00:33:00,970 --> 00:33:02,130
聚少离多
Not very.

589
00:33:03,960 --> 00:33:07,870
有一个人  我对她...
There is someone that I feel...

590
00:33:07,870 --> 00:33:09,380
她对你也是一样吗
Does she feel that way?

591
00:33:09,560 --> 00:33:10,830
有时吧
Sometimes.

592
00:33:11,510 --> 00:33:12,510
不够多
Not enough.

593
00:33:14,270 --> 00:33:16,780
我要去新墨西哥州了
You know, I'm going to New Mexico.

594
00:33:17,330 --> 00:33:19,230
去我的牧场  跟朋友们一起
To my ranch, with friends.

595
00:33:19,230 --> 00:33:20,280
你也来吧
You should come.

596
00:33:21,510 --> 00:33:22,880
我是说  和你丈夫一起
I meant, with your husband.

597
00:33:23,120 --> 00:33:24,340
是啊
Yes, you did.

598
00:33:24,650 --> 00:33:27,130
你明知道加不加这句话  结果都一样
Because you know it won't make a bit of difference.

599
00:33:31,500 --> 00:33:32,890
你为什么嫁给他
Why did you marry him?

600
00:33:33,120 --> 00:33:36,500
我那时很迷茫  他很温柔
I was lost, and... he was kind.

601
00:33:38,780 --> 00:33:39,760
迷茫
Lost?

602
00:33:40,200 --> 00:33:42,710
我上一任丈夫去世了
Well, my previous husband had died, and...

603
00:33:43,290 --> 00:33:45,590
28岁的我毫无准备就当了寡妇
at 28, I wasn't really ready to be a widow.

604
00:33:45,910 --> 00:33:47,840
-你第一任丈夫是谁  -无名小卒
- Who was your first husband? - Nobody.

605
00:33:48,020 --> 00:33:50,360
我第二任丈夫是乔·达莱特
My second husband was Joe Dallet.

606
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:52,630
他跟我一样也出身富裕
He was from money, like me,

607
00:33:52,630 --> 00:33:56,290
但他当时是俄亥俄州扬斯敦的工会组织者
but he was a union organizer in Youngstown, Ohio.

608
00:33:56,320 --> 00:33:57,510
我爱得疯狂
I fell hard.

609
00:33:58,380 --> 00:34:00,390
-有多疯狂  -在接下来的四年里
- How hard? - Hard enough to spend the next four years

610
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:01,700
甘愿仅靠豆子和煎饼果腹
living off beans and pancakes,

611
00:34:01,700 --> 00:34:04,200
在工厂门口发《每日工人》的那种疯狂
handing out the Daily Worker at factory gates.

612
00:34:05,250 --> 00:34:07,560
到1936年  我对乔说  我再也受不了了
By '36, I just told Joe I couldn't take it anymore.

613
00:34:07,560 --> 00:34:08,760
我退了党
Quit the party.

614
00:34:08,820 --> 00:34:10,300
一年之后  我又想跟他复合
A year later, I wanted him back.

615
00:34:10,300 --> 00:34:12,550
只要他  不要《每日工人》  然后...
Him, not the Daily Worker. And...

616
00:34:12,950 --> 00:34:15,090
他说  "好啊  我们去西班牙的路上见"
he said: "Swell, I'll meet you on my way to Spain."

617
00:34:15,090 --> 00:34:16,380
去为忠诚派而战吗
Went to fight for the Loyalists?

618
00:34:16,380 --> 00:34:18,450
然后他去参军了  我等啊等
And then he went to the brigades and I waited.

619
00:34:18,710 --> 00:34:19,610
然后
And...

620
00:34:21,230 --> 00:34:22,110
他上战场后
Joe got himself killed

621
00:34:22,120 --> 00:34:24,310
第一次从战壕探头就丢了命
first time he popped his head out of the trench.

622
00:34:25,560 --> 00:34:28,090
意识形态害死了乔  毫无意义
Ideology got Joe killed, for nothing.

623
00:34:28,090 --> 00:34:29,850
西班牙共和国可不是毫无意义
The Spanish Republic isn't nothing.

624
00:34:29,850 --> 00:34:31,540
我丈夫赔上我们两人的未来
My husband offered both our futures

625
00:34:31,540 --> 00:34:35,170
换来一颗本该射进泥滩的法西斯子弹击中他自己
to stop one fascist bullet from embedding itself in a mud bank.

626
00:34:35,980 --> 00:34:38,340
这就是毫无意义
That's the definition of nothing.

627
00:34:38,430 --> 00:34:40,600
-有点过于简化了  -是务实
- Seems a little reductive. - Pragmatic.

628
00:34:42,310 --> 00:34:43,580
结果我就落得这个境地了
Now here I am.

629
00:34:46,220 --> 00:34:47,830
管它现在是什么情况
Wherever the hell this is.

630
00:34:55,310 --> 00:34:57,870
我不希望你从别人口中听说
I didn't want you to hear it from anyone else.

631
00:35:00,550 --> 00:35:02,790
至少这次你没再送我花
At least you didn't bring me flowers.

632
00:35:10,040 --> 00:35:12,630
我们心里都清楚  你想要的不是我  吉恩
We both know I'm not what you want, Jean.

633
00:35:13,720 --> 00:35:15,860
对  可是以后我俩再也没可能了
Yeah, but it's a door closing.

634
00:35:16,410 --> 00:35:17,360
不
No.

635
00:35:19,430 --> 00:35:21,520
至少我不这么认为
Not as far as I'm concerned, no.

636
00:35:23,030 --> 00:35:25,410
你这就让她怀上了  动作够快
You knocked her up. Fast work.

637
00:35:25,410 --> 00:35:27,150
好男人是很抢手
Can't keep a good man down.

638
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:29,590
我是说她
I meant her.

639
00:35:30,250 --> 00:35:31,880
她知道她想要什么
She knew what she wanted.

640
00:35:31,900 --> 00:35:33,440
她丈夫怎么办
What about the husband?

641
00:35:33,640 --> 00:35:34,540
我们聊过了
We talked.

642
00:35:35,140 --> 00:35:36,470
他们打算离婚
They're getting a divorce,

643
00:35:36,480 --> 00:35:40,350
这样我俩就能赶在她显怀之前结婚
so we can get married before she starts showing.

644
00:35:40,350 --> 00:35:42,200
真体面啊
How civilized.

645
00:35:43,970 --> 00:35:45,230
你个傻子
You idiot.

646
00:35:45,440 --> 00:35:47,230
这是你们科学家的圈子
This is your community.

647
00:35:47,810 --> 00:35:50,440
你以为天才就能藐视规律了吗
You think the rules don't apply to the golden boy?

648
00:35:51,070 --> 00:35:52,920
才华确实能掩盖不少问题
Brilliance makes up for a lot.

649
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:55,320
这世上懂你的人不多
Don't alienate the only people in the world

650
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:57,300
别疏远他们
that understand what you do.

651
00:35:58,740 --> 00:36:00,440
没准哪天你会需要他们
One day you might need them.

652
00:36:00,440 --> 00:36:02,960
FAECT
F-a-e-c-t!

653
00:36:02,970 --> 00:36:07,350
建筑师  工程师  化学家与技师联盟
Federation of Architects, Engineers, Chemists and Technicians.

654
00:36:14,110 --> 00:36:16,250
洛马尼茨  他们一个月付你多少钱
Lomanitz, what do you get paid a month?

655
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:17,470
重点不是这个  劳伦斯
That's not the point, Lawrence.

656
00:36:17,470 --> 00:36:19,710
你们跟农民和码头工人
What do any of you have in common

657
00:36:19,710 --> 00:36:22,360
有什么共同点吗
with farm laborers and dock workers?

658
00:36:22,360 --> 00:36:23,250
有很多
Plenty.

659
00:36:24,910 --> 00:36:27,220
都出去  快
Everybody out. Now!

660
00:36:31,490 --> 00:36:32,480
你留下
Not you.

661
00:36:38,760 --> 00:36:39,860
你在干什么
What are you doing?

662
00:36:40,700 --> 00:36:41,930
工会而已
It's a trade union.

663
00:36:42,220 --> 00:36:43,770
满是共党的工会
Filled with communists.

664
00:36:43,770 --> 00:36:45,560
那又怎样  我又没入党
So? I haven't joined the party.

665
00:36:45,560 --> 00:36:47,360
正是因为这破事
They won't let me bring you onto the project

666
00:36:47,360 --> 00:36:48,720
他们不让我带你参加那个项目
because of this shit.

667
00:36:49,150 --> 00:36:51,200
连项目是干什么的都不让我告诉你
They won't even let me tell you what the project is.

668
00:36:52,010 --> 00:36:53,490
我知道是什么项目
Oh, I know what the project is.

669
00:36:53,850 --> 00:36:54,430
是吗
Oh, really?

670
00:36:54,430 --> 00:36:55,020
我们都听说了
We've all heard

671
00:36:55,020 --> 00:36:57,160
爱因斯坦和西拉德给罗斯福写信
about Einstein and Szilard's letter to Roosevelt

672
00:36:57,160 --> 00:36:58,630
提醒他德国人可能造出炸弹
warning him the Germans could make a bomb,

673
00:36:58,630 --> 00:37:02,140
我清楚纳粹有了炸弹就意味着什么
and I know what it means for the Nazis to have a bomb.

674
00:37:02,140 --> 00:37:03,140
难道我不清楚吗
And I don't?

675
00:37:03,620 --> 00:37:05,950
被他们赶进集中营的  不是你的同胞
It's not your people they're herding into camps.

676
00:37:06,480 --> 00:37:07,450
是我的
It's mine.

677
00:37:08,570 --> 00:37:11,180
你以为是我告诉了他们你的政治立场吗
You think that I tell them about your politics?

678
00:37:12,970 --> 00:37:14,960
下次你从集会回家的时候
The next time you're coming home from a meeting,

679
00:37:14,970 --> 00:37:17,190
从后视镜里看一眼
why don't you take a look in the rearview mirror,

680
00:37:17,210 --> 00:37:19,140
注意电话听筒的杂音
listen to the sounds on your phone line,

681
00:37:19,140 --> 00:37:22,340
别再这么天真了好吗
and stop being so goddamn naive?

682
00:37:23,390 --> 00:37:24,870
他们为什么会关心我做什么
Why would they care what I do?

683
00:37:24,930 --> 00:37:26,900
因为你不只是自命不凡
Because you're not just self-important,

684
00:37:26,900 --> 00:37:29,090
你是真的很重要
you're actually important.

685
00:37:32,260 --> 00:37:33,220
好吧
Okay.

686
00:37:34,730 --> 00:37:35,670
我明白了
I get it.

687
00:37:35,840 --> 00:37:37,850
你要是能再...
If you could just be a little more...

688
00:37:37,850 --> 00:37:40,670
务实一点  我会和洛马尼茨他们谈谈的
Pragmatic. I'll talk to Lomanitz, I'll talk to the others.

689
00:37:40,670 --> 00:37:42,300
不用担心  我能解决好
You don't have to worry, it's done.

690
00:37:42,730 --> 00:37:43,640
劳伦斯
Lawrence.

691
00:37:48,810 --> 00:37:50,220
那欢迎加入战争
Then welcome to the war.

692
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:53,270
我填写了第一份安全调查表
I filled out my first security questionnaire

693
00:37:53,270 --> 00:37:56,710
并被告知  我与左翼团体的联系
and was informed that my involvement with left-wing groups

694
00:37:56,710 --> 00:38:00,620
不会妨碍我为核项目工作
would not prove a bar to my working on the atomic program.

695
00:38:00,620 --> 00:38:03,360
为什么他与共产党人的关系
Why were his communist associations

696
00:38:03,360 --> 00:38:06,330
在战争期间没被视为安全风险
not seen as a security risk during the war?

697
00:38:06,330 --> 00:38:09,280
参议员先生  我不可能
Senator, I can't possibly answer for security clearance

698
00:38:09,280 --> 00:38:11,440
为在我认识此人几年前就获批的安全许可负责
granted years before I ever met the man.

699
00:38:11,440 --> 00:38:13,020
好吧  那之后呢
Fine. What about after?

700
00:38:13,450 --> 00:38:14,580
战后
After the war,

701
00:38:14,590 --> 00:38:15,600
奥本海默博士
Dr. Oppenheimer

702
00:38:15,600 --> 00:38:19,390
是世上最受敬重的科学家
was the most respected scientific voice in the world.

703
00:38:19,390 --> 00:38:21,480
因此我才请他来执掌高等研究院
That's why I asked him to run the Institute.

704
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:24,580
因此他为原子能委员会出谋划策
That's why he advised the Atomic Energy Commission.

705
00:38:24,580 --> 00:38:25,700
就这么简单
Simple as that.

706
00:38:26,130 --> 00:38:27,780
他们指控我什么
What are they accusing me of?

707
00:38:28,270 --> 00:38:29,290
我觉得他们只是想知道
I think they just want to know

708
00:38:29,290 --> 00:38:31,850
1947到1954年间
what happened between 1947 and 1954

709
00:38:31,850 --> 00:38:34,400
是什么让你改变了对奥本海默安全许可的决定
to change your mind on Oppenheimer's security clearance.

710
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:35,470
不是我
I didn't.

711
00:38:35,610 --> 00:38:38,740
我是原子能委员会的主席
I was chair of the AEC, but it wasn't me

712
00:38:38,990 --> 00:38:41,790
-但对罗伯特的指控不是我提的  -那是谁
- that brought the charges against Robert. - Who did?

713
00:38:41,790 --> 00:38:44,350
某个国会原子能联合委员会的前成员
Some former staff member of the Joint Congressional Committee.

714
00:38:44,350 --> 00:38:47,140
他叫波登  是个激进的反共分子
He was a rabid anti-communist named Borden.

715
00:38:47,150 --> 00:38:49,840
