从奥本海默的安全档案可知
Reading Oppenheimer's security file,

722
00:39:05,820 --> 00:39:07,360
他的共产党弟弟
his communist brother,

723
00:39:07,370 --> 00:39:10,320
弟媳  未婚妻  好友  妻子
sister-in-law, fiancée, best friend, wife.

724
00:39:10,470 --> 00:39:12,860
更不用说薛瓦利埃事件了
That's before we even get to the Chevalier incident.

725
00:39:12,860 --> 00:39:15,940
但波登是怎么拿到奥本海默的安全档案的
But how would Borden have access to Oppenheimer's security file?

726
00:39:16,200 --> 00:39:17,880
有人给他的
Because somebody gave it to him.

727
00:39:19,190 --> 00:39:21,670
某个想让罗伯特闭嘴的人
Somebody who wanted Robert silenced.

728
00:39:22,150 --> 00:39:23,800
-谁  -谁知道呢
- Who? - Who knows?

729
00:39:23,800 --> 00:39:25,260
罗伯特没照顾到
Robert didn't take care

730
00:39:25,260 --> 00:39:28,020
华盛顿那些政治掮客的想法
not to upset the power brokers in Washington.

731
00:39:28,580 --> 00:39:31,320
他对原子能的看法坚定不移
His opinions on the atom became definitive,

732
00:39:31,360 --> 00:39:34,130
对我们这些凡人也不常有耐心
and he wasn't always patient with us mere mortals.

733
00:39:37,650 --> 00:39:39,950
我就遭受过不少苛刻的对待
I came in for plenty of harsh treatment.

734
00:39:39,950 --> 00:39:43,440
之前有次原子能委员会
There was an AEC vote

735
00:39:43,460 --> 00:39:45,830
投票表决同位素到挪威的出口
on the export of isotopes to Norway,

736
00:39:45,830 --> 00:39:48,590
他们拉上罗伯特  让我出尽洋相
and they drafted in Robert to make me look like a fool.

737
00:39:48,590 --> 00:39:49,920
不过奥本海默博士
But Dr. Oppenheimer,

738
00:39:49,920 --> 00:39:51,810
我们已听施特劳斯上将说
we've already heard from Admiral Strauss

739
00:39:51,810 --> 00:39:55,120
我们的敌人可能会利用这些同位素
that these isotopes could be useful to our enemies

740
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:56,510
制造核武器
in the production of atomic weapons.

741
00:39:56,510 --> 00:39:59,930
议员先生  造核武器还可能用到铲子呢
Congressman, you could use a shovel in making atomic weapons.

742
00:39:59,930 --> 00:40:00,990
的确会用到
In fact, you do.

743
00:40:00,990 --> 00:40:03,970
造核武器还可能用到一瓶啤酒
You could use a bottle of beer in making atomic weapons.

744
00:40:03,970 --> 00:40:04,920
的确会用到
In fact, you do.

745
00:40:04,920 --> 00:40:08,770
要我说同位素还没有电子元件有用
I'd say isotopes are less useful than electronic components,

746
00:40:08,770 --> 00:40:10,720
但比三明治有用
but more useful than a sandwich.

747
00:40:14,650 --> 00:40:16,590
天才不一定有智慧
Genius is no guarantee of wisdom.

748
00:40:17,290 --> 00:40:20,180
这人为何洞悉一切却又如此盲目
How could this man who saw so much be so blind?

749
00:40:29,580 --> 00:40:30,620
吉蒂
Kitty?

750
00:40:35,710 --> 00:40:36,650
吉蒂
Kitty?

751
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:39,170
吉蒂
Kitty.

752
00:40:39,690 --> 00:40:40,720
那个项目
The project.

753
00:40:41,580 --> 00:40:42,520
我加入了
I'm in.

754
00:40:43,720 --> 00:40:46,170
-我加入了  -来庆祝吧
- I'm in! - Let's celebrate.

755
00:40:52,120 --> 00:40:53,370
你不该去哄哄他吗
Shouldn't you go to him?

756
00:40:58,400 --> 00:41:01,600
我他妈哄了他一天了
I have been going to him all fucking day.

757
00:41:27,290 --> 00:41:29,120
我不知道该如何开口
I don't know how to say this.

758
00:41:30,420 --> 00:41:31,890
我羞于启齿
I'm ashamed to ask.

759
00:41:32,180 --> 00:41:33,070
说吧
Anything.

760
00:41:34,110 --> 00:41:36,140
-拜托照顾彼得  -没问题
- Take Peter. - Sure.

761
00:41:36,140 --> 00:41:38,400
不  是照顾一阵子  哈康
No, for a while, Haak.

762
00:41:38,810 --> 00:41:39,800
一阵子
A while.

763
00:41:42,100 --> 00:41:45,460
-吉蒂知道你来这里了吗  -她当然知道
- Does Kitty know you're here? - Yes, of course she knows.

764
00:41:46,240 --> 00:41:47,600
她当然知道
Of course she knows.

765
00:41:48,560 --> 00:41:51,180
我们太差劲了  自私  差劲
We're awful people. Selfish, awful people.

766
00:41:53,410 --> 00:41:54,480
算了当我没问
Forget I asked.

767
00:41:54,480 --> 00:41:56,570
自私  差劲的人
Selfish, awful people,

768
00:41:56,570 --> 00:41:59,500
是意识不到他们的自私和差劲的
they don't know they're selfish and awful.

769
00:41:59,690 --> 00:42:01,450
坐吧
Sit, sit, sit.

770
00:42:02,550 --> 00:42:06,830
罗伯特  你能看到现实世界以外的另一个世界
Robert, you see beyond the world we live in.

771
00:42:08,230 --> 00:42:10,470
是要付出代价的
There is a price to be paid for that.

772
00:42:10,850 --> 00:42:12,230
我们当然会帮你
Of course we'll help you.

773
00:42:23,420 --> 00:42:25,270
一切都在改变  罗伯特
Everything's changing, Robert.

774
00:42:25,900 --> 00:42:27,610
有了孩子自然会改变...
Having a child was always going to change...

775
00:42:27,610 --> 00:42:31,340
不  世界在转向新的方向
No, the world is pivoting in some new direction.

776
00:42:32,210 --> 00:42:33,590
在改革
Reforming.

777
00:42:35,860 --> 00:42:37,380
这是你的机会
This is your moment.

778
00:42:38,890 --> 00:42:40,510
我们在召集人马  研究...
We're putting together a group to study...

779
00:42:40,510 --> 00:42:42,170
不是"我们"
We shouldn't be doing anything.

780
00:42:42,170 --> 00:42:43,190
是"你"
You should.

781
00:42:44,060 --> 00:42:45,880
劳伦斯搞不定的
Lawrence won't get this done.

782
00:42:46,310 --> 00:42:48,420
托尔曼和拉比也不能  你可以
Or Tolman or Rabi. You will.

783
00:42:57,660 --> 00:42:59,020
那些穿军装的是什么人
Who are the uniforms?

784
00:43:00,120 --> 00:43:01,500
我还以为你知道呢
I thought you might know.

785
00:43:03,760 --> 00:43:04,990
奥本海默博士
Dr. Oppenheimer.

786
00:43:06,430 --> 00:43:09,790
我是格罗夫斯上校  这位是尼科斯中校
I'm Colonel Groves. This is Lieutenant Colonel Nichols.

787
00:43:09,790 --> 00:43:11,220
送去干洗
Have that dry cleaned.

788
00:43:16,700 --> 00:43:19,210
如果你这么对待一位中校的话
Well, if that's how you treat a lieutenant colonel,

789
00:43:19,210 --> 00:43:22,870
我不敢想你会怎样对一名小小的物理学家
I'd hate to see how you treat a... humble physicist.

790
00:43:23,010 --> 00:43:24,810
等我以后遇到了你就知道了
If I ever meet one, I'll let you know.

791
00:43:26,360 --> 00:43:28,180
全世界都在打仗
Theaters of combat all over the world,

792
00:43:28,180 --> 00:43:30,070
我却只能留在华盛顿
but I have to stay in Washington.

793
00:43:30,520 --> 00:43:32,740
-为什么  -我建了五角大楼
- Why? - I built the Pentagon.

794
00:43:32,750 --> 00:43:33,930
要员们很喜欢
The brass likes it so much,

795
00:43:33,930 --> 00:43:37,400
于是又让我掌管曼哈顿工程区
they made me take over the Manhattan Engineer District.

796
00:43:37,880 --> 00:43:40,990
-那是什么  -别装了
- Which is? - Don't be a smartass.

797
00:43:40,990 --> 00:43:42,070
你清楚得很
You know damn well what it is.

798
00:43:42,070 --> 00:43:44,590
你和全国物理系半数教职员工都清楚
You and half of every physics department across the country.

799
00:43:44,590 --> 00:43:46,360
这是首要问题
That's problem number one.

800
00:43:46,610 --> 00:43:47,730
我还以为搞到足够多的铀矿石
I thought problem number one

801
00:43:47,730 --> 00:43:49,980
才是首要问题
would be securing enough uranium ore.

802
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:53,550
-一千两百吨  我上任那天就买下了  -那加工呢
- 1,200 tons, bought the day I took charge. - Processing?

803
00:43:53,550 --> 00:43:55,640
刚在田纳西州的橡树岭动工
Just broke ground at Oak Ridge, Tennessee.

804
00:43:56,830 --> 00:43:58,910
现在我在物色项目负责人
Now I'm looking for a project director.

805
00:43:59,500 --> 00:44:00,860
想到我了
And my name came up?

806
00:44:01,020 --> 00:44:01,910
不是
Nope.

807
00:44:02,860 --> 00:44:05,200
虽然你把量子物理学带到了美国
Even though you brought quantum physics to America,

808
00:44:05,200 --> 00:44:06,620
让我还挺好奇的
which made me curious.

809
00:44:07,110 --> 00:44:08,410
你调查出什么了
What have you found out?

810
00:44:09,470 --> 00:44:13,380
你是个半吊子  花花公子  疑似共产党
You're a dilettante, a womanizer, a suspected communist.

811
00:44:13,380 --> 00:44:14,730
我是支持新政的民主党
I'm a New Deal Democrat.

812
00:44:14,730 --> 00:44:16,140
我说了是"疑似"
I said "suspected".

813
00:44:16,500 --> 00:44:20,560
情绪多变  做作  高傲  神经质
Unstable, theatrical, egotistical, neurotic.

814
00:44:20,560 --> 00:44:21,650
没找到优点  是吧
Nothing good, no?

815
00:44:21,660 --> 00:44:23,590
甚至没句  "他很聪明  但是"
Not even "he's brilliant, but..."

816
00:44:23,590 --> 00:44:26,550
聪明是你们这个圈子最基本的品质  所以没有
Well, brilliance is taken for granted in your circle, so no.

817
00:44:27,000 --> 00:44:28,730
唯一一个夸了你的是
No, the only person who had anything good to say

818
00:44:28,730 --> 00:44:30,140
理查德·托尔曼
was Richard Tolman.

819
00:44:30,710 --> 00:44:32,660
托尔曼觉得你为人正直
Tolman thinks you have integrity,

820
00:44:32,660 --> 00:44:34,860
但我还是觉得
but he also strikes me as a guy

821
00:44:34,860 --> 00:44:37,520
他看人的本事不如科研
who knows more about science than people.

822
00:44:37,520 --> 00:44:38,730
但你还是来了
Yet here you are.

823
00:44:39,580 --> 00:44:41,360
你不太信任人
You don't take much on trust.

824
00:44:41,360 --> 00:44:43,200
我什么都不信任
I don't take anything on trust.

825
00:44:46,910 --> 00:44:48,660
你怎么没得诺贝尔奖
Why don't you have a Nobel Prize?

826
00:44:48,660 --> 00:44:49,630
你怎么没当上将军
Why aren't you a general?

827
00:44:49,630 --> 00:44:50,880
这事要是成了就当上了
They're making me one for this.

828
00:44:50,880 --> 00:44:52,350
说不定我也一样
Perhaps I'll have the same luck.

829
00:44:52,350 --> 00:44:53,850
造炸弹能得诺贝尔奖
The Nobel Prize for making a bomb?

830
00:44:53,850 --> 00:44:55,990
阿尔弗雷德·诺贝尔发明了硝酸甘油炸药
Alfred Nobel invented dynamite.

831
00:44:58,700 --> 00:45:00,180
你打算怎么做
So how would you proceed?

832
00:45:01,910 --> 00:45:02,630
你说的是
You're talking about

833
00:45:02,630 --> 00:45:06,620
抢在纳粹之前
turning theory into a practical weapon system

834
00:45:06,740 --> 00:45:08,130
把理论变成可用的武器
faster than the Nazis.

835
00:45:08,130 --> 00:45:09,910
他们已经比我们提前了12个月
Who have a 12-month head start.

836
00:45:09,910 --> 00:45:12,200
-是18个月  -你怎么知道
- 18. - How could you possibly know that?

837
00:45:12,200 --> 00:45:14,430
我们的快中子研究花了六个月
Our fast neutron research took six months.

838
00:45:14,430 --> 00:45:15,880
纳粹指派的研究负责人
The man they've undoubtedly put in charge

839
00:45:15,880 --> 00:45:17,420
肯定不会卡在这上面
will have made that leap instantly.

840
00:45:17,420 --> 00:45:18,790
你觉得他们派谁负责了
Who do you think they put in charge?

841
00:45:18,790 --> 00:45:19,870
维尔纳·海森堡
Werner Heisenberg.

842
00:45:19,870 --> 00:45:22,890
他是我见过对原子结构
He has the most intuitive understanding of atomic structure

843
00:45:22,890 --> 00:45:24,080
有着最直观认识的人
I have ever seen.

844
00:45:24,080 --> 00:45:25,750
-你了解他的研究吗  -我了解他这个人
- You know his work? - I know him,

845
00:45:25,920 --> 00:45:28,200
就像我了解瓦尔特·博特  冯·魏茨泽克  迪布纳
just like I know Walther Bothe, von Weizsäcker, Diebner.

846
00:45:28,200 --> 00:45:30,190
硬碰硬比速度的话  德国人必胜
In a straight race, the Germans win.

847
00:45:30,630 --> 00:45:32,580
-我们有一线希望  -是什么
- We've got one hope. - Which is?

848
00:45:33,700 --> 00:45:35,070
反犹太主义
Antisemitism.

849
00:45:36,800 --> 00:45:37,650
什么
What?

850
00:45:37,820 --> 00:45:40,490
希特勒说量子物理学是"犹太人的科学"
Hitler called quantum physics "Jewish science".

851
00:45:40,490 --> 00:45:41,920
跟爱因斯坦当面说的
Said it right to Einstein's face.

852
00:45:41,920 --> 00:45:45,450
我们唯一的希望就是希特勒被仇恨蒙蔽
Our one hope is that Hitler is so blinded by hate

853
00:45:45,450 --> 00:45:47,510
拒绝给海森堡提供足够的资源
that he's denied Heisenberg proper resources,

854
00:45:47,510 --> 00:45:49,420
因为那将耗费海量资源
because it'll take vast resources.

855
00:45:49,420 --> 00:45:51,050
而我国最优秀的科学家齐心协力
Our nation's best scientists working together.

856
00:45:51,050 --> 00:45:52,220
但现在  大家散落在各地
Right now, they're scattered.

857
00:45:52,220 --> 00:45:54,220
正好做到了权限分隔
Which gives us compartmentalization.

858
00:45:54,230 --> 00:45:57,220
只有让所有人都清楚情况  才能高效工作
All minds have to see the whole task to contribute efficiently.

859
00:45:57,220 --> 00:45:59,450
安全保密问题可能会让我们落后
Poor security may cost us the race.

860
00:45:59,450 --> 00:46:00,960
但低效一定会
Inefficiency will.

861
00:46:01,530 --> 00:46:03,450
反正德国人比我们知道得更多
The Germans know more than us anyway.

862
00:46:03,450 --> 00:46:04,820
苏联人可不一定
The Russians don't.

863
00:46:06,340 --> 00:46:09,600
慢着  我们在和谁打仗
Remind me, who are we at war with?

864
00:46:09,920 --> 00:46:10,880
鉴于你的过去
Somebody with your past

865
00:46:10,920 --> 00:46:14,590
你肯定不想让人觉得你忽视了保密工作
doesn't want to be seen downplaying the importance of security

866
00:46:14,590 --> 00:46:16,500
没提防我们的共产党盟友
from our communist allies.

867
00:46:17,040 --> 00:46:19,550
有道理  但是  不
Point taken, but... no.

868
00:46:19,630 --> 00:46:21,260
你不能跟我说不
You don't get to say no to me.

869
00:46:21,270 --> 00:46:23,500
我的职责就是在你搞错时跟你说不
It's my job to say no to you when you're wrong.

870
00:46:24,070 --> 00:46:25,810
所以你接下这份工作了
So you have the job now?

871
00:46:26,220 --> 00:46:27,480
我再想想
I'm considering it.

872
00:46:30,440 --> 00:46:32,890
我明白你的名声从何而来了
I'm starting to see where you got your reputation.

873
00:46:34,150 --> 00:46:35,790
我最喜欢的回应是
My favorite response:

874
00:46:36,470 --> 00:46:39,030
"奥本海默连汉堡摊都管不好"
"Oppenheimer couldn't run a hamburger stand."

875
00:46:40,570 --> 00:46:41,620
我是不行
I couldn't.

876
00:46:43,730 --> 00:46:46,060
但我能管好曼哈顿计划
But I can run the Manhattan Project.

877
00:46:47,110 --> 00:46:48,930
有一个办法保持平衡
There's a way to balance these things.

878
00:46:49,760 --> 00:46:52,960
