01:05:44,840 --> 01:05:46,040
尼科斯
Nichols?

1229
01:05:47,510 --> 01:05:50,110
我还没有收到我的安全许可获批的消息
I still haven't heard that my security clearance has been approved.

1230
01:05:50,120 --> 01:05:52,150
-的确还没  -我明天要去芝加哥
- It hasn't. - I'm going to Chicago tomorrow.

1231
01:05:52,210 --> 01:05:53,370
你得等
Well, you should wait.

1232
01:05:53,930 --> 01:05:56,500
你知道纳粹领先我们两年时间吗
You are aware that the Nazis have a two-year head start?

1233
01:05:56,500 --> 01:05:58,470
奥本海默博士  您的安全许可
Dr. Oppenheimer, the fact that your security clearance

1234
01:05:58,470 --> 01:06:00,900
难以通过并不是我的错
is proving difficult to obtain is not my fault.

1235
01:06:00,910 --> 01:06:01,930
是您自己的
It's yours.

1236
01:06:01,930 --> 01:06:03,780
也许不是你的错  但应该由你解决
It may not be your fault, but it's your problem.

1237
01:06:03,790 --> 01:06:04,930
无论如何我要去
Because I'm going.

1238
01:06:05,490 --> 01:06:07,750
有多少人参与了这种
And how many people were in these, uh...

1239
01:06:08,330 --> 01:06:10,370
公开讨论
open discussions?

1240
01:06:10,440 --> 01:06:12,780
太多了  本应按规章做好权限分隔的
Too many. Compartmentalization was supposed to be the protocol.

1241
01:06:12,780 --> 01:06:14,330
我们当时在与纳粹竞速
We were in a race against the Nazis.

1242
01:06:14,330 --> 01:06:16,590
现在是与苏联竞速
And now the race is against the Soviets.

1243
01:06:16,590 --> 01:06:17,710
我们不发起比赛就不用比
Not unless we start it.

1244
01:06:17,710 --> 01:06:21,520
罗伯特  他们刚刚打响了发令枪
Robert, they just fired the starting gun.

1245
01:06:21,810 --> 01:06:24,040
他们用的是什么引爆装置
What's the nature of the device they detonated?

1246
01:06:24,170 --> 01:06:27,750
看数据可能是一枚钚内爆装置
Data indicates it may have been a plutonium implosion device.

1247
01:06:27,750 --> 01:06:30,570
正是你们在洛斯阿拉莫斯造的那种
Like the one you built at Los Alamos.

1248
01:06:30,810 --> 01:06:32,080
苏联人已经有了原子弹
The Russians have a bomb.

1249
01:06:32,650 --> 01:06:33,750
杜鲁门需要知晓下一步
Truman needs to know what's next.

1250
01:06:33,750 --> 01:06:36,150
下一步  军备谈判
What's next? Arms talks.

1251
01:06:36,150 --> 01:06:37,470
-军备谈判  -很显然
- Arms talks? - Obviously.

1252
01:06:38,670 --> 01:06:41,640
氢弹呢  杜鲁门知道吗
What about the Super? Does Truman even know about it?

1253
01:06:41,640 --> 01:06:43,170
我们有没有作过汇报
Did we brief him on that?

1254
01:06:43,320 --> 01:06:44,610
没有专门汇报过
Not specifically.

1255
01:06:44,750 --> 01:06:47,760
我们仍不知道氢弹在技术上是否可行
We still don't know if a hydrogen bomb is technically feasible.

1256
01:06:47,770 --> 01:06:49,980
好  就我所知这是泰勒提出的
Right, my understanding is that Teller proposed it.

1257
01:06:49,990 --> 01:06:51,190
-是的  -在洛斯阿拉莫斯提出的
- Yes. - At Los Alamos?

1258
01:06:51,190 --> 01:06:53,560
泰勒的设计非常不切实际
Teller's designs have always been wildly impractical.

1259
01:06:53,560 --> 01:06:56,850
按他的办法投弹要用牛车  而不是飞机
You'd have to deliver by oxcart, not airplane.

1260
01:06:56,850 --> 01:06:58,530
-奥比  -抱歉  劳伦斯博士
- Oppie! - I'm sorry, Dr. Lawrence,

1261
01:06:58,530 --> 01:07:00,230
您有话要说
do you want to comment?

1262
01:07:01,660 --> 01:07:02,700
没有
No.

1263
01:07:04,770 --> 01:07:07,130
因为如果氢弹能让我们再度领先
Because if it can put us ahead again,

1264
01:07:07,340 --> 01:07:12,030
美国总统就应该知道这件事
the President of the United States needs to know about it.

1265
01:07:13,800 --> 01:07:16,830
如果苏联人已经通过洛斯阿拉莫斯的间谍知道了
And if the Russians know about it already from a spy,

1266
01:07:16,960 --> 01:07:19,900
我们必须着手研究了
at Los Alamos, then we've got to get going.

1267
01:07:19,900 --> 01:07:22,810
没有证据表明洛斯阿拉莫斯存在间谍
There's no proof there was a spy at Los Alamos.

1268
01:07:22,850 --> 01:07:23,870
罗伯特
Robert.

1269
01:07:28,940 --> 01:07:30,430
他们的实验室在足球场底下
They put it under the football stadium?

1270
01:07:30,630 --> 01:07:32,130
场地早就停用了
The field's not in use anymore.

1271
01:07:32,720 --> 01:07:33,890
不相上下
Just as well.

1272
01:07:36,780 --> 01:07:38,720
-奥比  -费米博士
- Oppie! - Dr. Fermi.

1273
01:07:38,870 --> 01:07:41,330
你怎么样  还好吗
Come stai, tutto bene?

1274
01:07:41,460 --> 01:07:44,440
-我听说你坐拥一座小镇  -没错  欢迎参观
- I hear you've got a little town. - Yes, come and see.

1275
01:07:45,700 --> 01:07:49,060
在那种地方谁能正常思考
Who could think straight in a place like that, huh?

1276
01:07:49,830 --> 01:07:51,680
大家都会被逼疯的
Everybody will go crazy.

1277
01:07:52,620 --> 01:07:55,090
谢谢你的信任  西拉德
Thank you the vote of confidence, Szilard.

1278
01:07:56,270 --> 01:07:59,080
这些也值得记
Do we really... do we really need that in the notes?

1279
01:07:59,980 --> 01:08:01,370
你们要试验吗
Are you gonna try it out?

1280
01:08:01,830 --> 01:08:02,820
已经做过了
We did.

1281
01:08:03,430 --> 01:08:06,780
首次自持续链式核反应
The first self-sustaining nuclear chain reaction.

1282
01:08:07,400 --> 01:08:08,470
格罗夫斯没告诉你吗
Didn't Groves tell you?

1283
01:08:09,490 --> 01:08:10,660
没有
No.

1284
01:08:18,250 --> 01:08:19,550
奥本海默博士
Dr. Oppenheimer?

1285
01:08:20,480 --> 01:08:21,880
我找过人力
I tried personnel.

1286
01:08:21,880 --> 01:08:24,540
-他们问我会不会打字  -你会吗
- They asked if I could type. - Can you?

1287
01:08:24,550 --> 01:08:27,690
哈佛的化学研究生课程忘了教这个
Harvard forgot to teach that on the graduate chemistry course.

1288
01:08:29,410 --> 01:08:31,900
康登  让霍尼格夫人加入钚小组
Condon, put Mrs. Hornig here on the plutonium team.

1289
01:08:37,670 --> 01:08:39,630
你们去芝加哥干什么
What the hell were you doing in Chicago?

1290
01:08:39,830 --> 01:08:41,290
-参观大都会博物馆  -为什么
- Visiting the met. - Why?

1291
01:08:41,290 --> 01:08:42,700
-你不能...  -为什么
- You can't... - Why?

1292
01:08:42,700 --> 01:08:43,900
因为我们完全有权
Because we, we have every right...

1293
01:08:43,900 --> 01:08:48,200
你有什么权利我说了算  一点不多  一点不少
You have just the rights that I give you. No more, no less.

1294
01:08:48,460 --> 01:08:50,420
我们都是成年人  齐心协力做一个项目
We are adults trying to run a project here.

1295
01:08:50,420 --> 01:08:51,770
这太荒谬了
This is ridiculous.

1296
01:08:52,160 --> 01:08:53,150
说话啊
Tell him!

1297
01:08:54,830 --> 01:08:57,490
权限分隔是我们认同的规章制度
Compartmentalization is the protocol we agreed to.

1298
01:08:58,680 --> 01:09:01,890
我受够这个疯人院了  这种条件谁还能安心工作
Enough of this madhouse. Nobody can work under these conditions.

1299
01:09:01,890 --> 01:09:05,970
告诉你吧  大将军  我不干了
You know what? Generalissimo, I quit!

1300
01:09:06,300 --> 01:09:07,520
可太谢谢你了
Thanks for nothing.

1301
01:09:09,990 --> 01:09:11,230
没了他更好
Better off without him.

1302
01:09:12,800 --> 01:09:15,890
你不是更应该担心他的保密问题吗
Aren't you more concerned about his discretion out there?

1303
01:09:16,680 --> 01:09:17,940
找人做掉他就好了
We'll have him killed.

1304
01:09:20,080 --> 01:09:21,310
开玩笑的
I'm just kidding.

1305
01:09:22,150 --> 01:09:24,070
不必  他讨厌的是我  不是美国
No, he hates me, not America.

1306
01:09:24,480 --> 01:09:27,130
可是将军  不是所有人都像我一样有把柄可抓
You know, General, not everyone has levers to pull like mine.

1307
01:09:27,890 --> 01:09:29,250
我不太明白
I don't think I understand.

1308
01:09:29,460 --> 01:09:31,800
你招募我不是因为宽恕了我过去的左翼倾向
You didn't hire me despite my left-wing past.

1309
01:09:31,800 --> 01:09:33,370
恰恰因为我的过去你才招募了我
You hired me because of it.

1310
01:09:34,150 --> 01:09:35,960
这样你就能控制我
So you could control me.

1311
01:09:36,520 --> 01:09:38,230
不  我做事没有这么含蓄
No, I'm not that subtle.

1312
01:09:38,880 --> 01:09:40,290
我只是个普通的大头兵罢了
I'm just a humble soldier.

1313
01:09:40,580 --> 01:09:42,500
你既不普通  也不是大头兵
You're neither humble, nor just a soldier.

1314
01:09:42,500 --> 01:09:44,390
你在麻省理工学过工程学
You studied engineering at MIT.

1315
01:09:44,390 --> 01:09:46,560
-被你发现了  -既然我们已经互相理解
- Guilty as charged. - Well, now we understand each other,

1316
01:09:46,570 --> 01:09:48,440
也许你现在可以帮我拿到安全许可
perhaps you can get me my security clearance,

1317
01:09:48,450 --> 01:09:50,570
让我继续为你创造奇迹
so I can perform this miracle for you.

1318
01:09:56,540 --> 01:09:57,180
格罗夫斯将军
General Groves,

1319
01:09:57,180 --> 01:10:00,180
您在任命奥本海默博士的时候
were you aware of Dr. Oppenheimer's left-wing associations

1320
01:10:00,180 --> 01:10:01,400
是否了解他与左翼存在联系
when you appointed him?

1321
01:10:01,410 --> 01:10:03,450
我知道有人对此有所怀疑
I was aware that there were suspicions about him.

1322
01:10:03,450 --> 01:10:06,680
我知道他的身份背景极其自由派
I was aware he had a very extreme liberal background.

1323
01:10:06,690 --> 01:10:07,490
在你看来
In your opinion,

1324
01:10:07,490 --> 01:10:10,140
他是否有意识地做出过不忠于国家的行为
would he ever consciously commit a disloyal act?

1325
01:10:10,140 --> 01:10:11,770
如果他做过  那我会很惊讶
I would be amazed if he did.

1326
01:10:11,770 --> 01:10:14,600
所以你完全信任他的忠诚吗
So you had complete confidence in his integrity?

1327
01:10:14,640 --> 01:10:16,110
在洛斯阿拉莫斯是的
At Los Alamos, yes.

1328
01:10:16,110 --> 01:10:17,520
我真正了解他就是在那里
Which is where I really knew him.

1329
01:10:17,530 --> 01:10:19,970
你知道在这个项目中  你的安全官员曾建议你
Do you know that your security officers on the project

1330
01:10:19,970 --> 01:10:22,310
不要给奥本海默博士发放安全许可吗
advised you against the clearance of Dr. Oppenheimer?

1331
01:10:22,310 --> 01:10:26,430
要不是我坚持  他们不能  也不会给他安全许可
They could not, and would not, clear him until I insisted.

1332
01:10:26,430 --> 01:10:28,320
也就是说  你对奥本海默博士的
And it's safe to say that you had pretty good knowledge

1333
01:10:28,320 --> 01:10:30,920
-安全档案的内容了然于胸  -是的
- of Dr. Oppenheimer's security file. - I did.

1334
01:10:31,780 --> 01:10:33,010
那么今天我其实只剩下一个问题
Well, then there's only really one question

1335
01:10:33,070 --> 01:10:34,410
希望得到解答了
I need answered here today.

1336
01:10:34,410 --> 01:10:36,500
按照现行的原子能委员会准则
In light of the current AEC guidelines,

1337
01:10:36,590 --> 01:10:38,890
你今天还会给奥本海默博士发放安全许可吗
would you clear Dr. Oppenheimer today?

1338
01:10:39,240 --> 01:10:40,570
你手头有这个准则吗
Do you have the guidelines?

1339
01:10:48,320 --> 01:10:50,680
按照现行的原子能委员会准则
Under current AEC guidelines,

1340
01:10:50,750 --> 01:10:53,880
你今天还会给奥本海默博士发放安全许可吗
would you clear Dr. Oppenheimer today?

1341
01:11:05,940 --> 01:11:07,610
物理和新墨西哥州是吧
Physics and New Mexico, huh?

1342
01:11:09,070 --> 01:11:11,540
老天爷  这一路可真够远的
My god. What a trek.

1343
01:11:12,120 --> 01:11:13,510
所以你需要个联络员
That's why you need a liaison.

1344
01:11:13,580 --> 01:11:14,810
我要让洛马尼茨来干
I'm appointing Lomanitz.

1345
01:11:16,180 --> 01:11:18,210
你不会有事的  这边请  先生们
You're gonna be okay. This way, gentlemen.

1346
01:11:28,440 --> 01:11:30,310
-劳伦斯博士  -莱斯利
- Dr. Lawrence. - Leslie.

1347
01:11:30,950 --> 01:11:33,070
我想提醒你一句我们在伯克利谈的内容
I'd like to remind you what we talked about at Berkeley.

1348
01:11:33,120 --> 01:11:34,970
权限分隔  我完全理解
Compartmentalization, I understand completely.

1349
01:11:50,330 --> 01:11:51,660
伯克利向大家问好
Greetings from Berkeley.

1350
01:11:51,810 --> 01:11:53,620
我来是为了和大家通报我们的进展
I am here to update you on our progress

1351
01:11:53,620 --> 01:11:54,900
并听取大家的意见的
and solicit your input.

1352
01:11:55,090 --> 01:11:57,610
因此  我不得不分享几件
To do so, I am going to have to share a few things that

1353
01:11:57,610 --> 01:11:59,280
格罗夫斯将军不让我说的事
General Groves told me not to.

1354
01:12:00,020 --> 01:12:02,990
抱歉将军  我说的是我理解  而不是我同意
Sorry General, I said I understood, not that I agreed.

1355
01:12:03,320 --> 01:12:06,340
好了  先生们  说正事
Okay. Gentlemen, to business!

1356
01:12:06,710 --> 01:12:08,730
有传言说洛斯阿拉莫斯
There were rumors of espionage

1357
01:12:08,730 --> 01:12:11,130
-有间谍  -毫无根据
- at Los Alamos. - Unsubstantiated.

1358
01:12:11,130 --> 01:12:13,170
我听说项目里有
I'm told that there were communists

1359
01:12:13,170 --> 01:12:14,540
-共产党  -我们并没有明明知情还雇用...
- on the project. - We didn't knowingly employ...

1360
01:12:14,540 --> 01:12:16,910
我只想知道  他们中是否有人
I just want to know, were any of them involved

1361
01:12:16,910 --> 01:12:18,450
参与了关于氢弹的讨论
in discussions of the Super?

1362
01:12:18,500 --> 01:12:21,130
我似乎记得你要求让你弟弟来洛斯阿拉莫斯
I seem to remember you demanding your brother come to Los Alamos.

1363
01:12:21,130 --> 01:12:22,840
我弟弟那时候已经不是共产党了
My brother had left the party by then.

1364
01:12:22,840 --> 01:12:24,040
洛马尼茨呢
What about Lomanitz?

1365
01:12:24,040 --> 01:12:26,100
洛马尼茨从来不是洛斯阿拉莫斯的工作人员
Lomanitz was never employed at Los Alamos.

1366
01:12:26,100 --> 01:12:27,230
他只是联络员
He was a liaison.

1367
01:12:27,330 --> 01:12:28,420
我们的安保没有问题
Our security was tight,

1368
01:12:28,420 --> 01:12:29,950
前中校尼科斯很清楚这一点
as former Colonel Nichols well knows.

1369
01:12:29,950 --> 01:12:31,200
鉴于项目涉及的人员
Our security was as tight as it could be

1370
01:12:31,200 --> 01:12:32,710
我们的安保只能说尽可能严格
given the personalities involved,

1371
01:12:32,710 --> 01:12:34,010
但确实有人试图窃密
but attempts were made.

1372
01:12:34,040 --> 01:12:36,810
-这话是什么意思  -我们都看过他的档案
- What is that supposed to mean? - We've all read his file here.

1373
01:12:37,970 --> 01:12:39,810
难道还需要说吉恩·塔特洛克的事吗
Do we need to talk about Jean Tatlock?

1374
01:12:41,390 --> 01:12:43,130
或者薛瓦利埃事件
Or the Chevalier incident?

1375
01:12:47,340 --> 01:12:48,490
失陪
Excuse me.

1376
01:12:51,380 --> 01:12:53,240
洛马尼茨  一号线
Lomanitz, line one!

1377
01:12:59,980 --> 01:13:01,010
喂  罗西
Hello, Rossi.

1378
01:13:01,370 --> 01:13:02,340
什么
What?

1379
01:13:03,060 --> 01:13:04,310
好的  冷静
Okay, just calm down.

1380
01:13:05,200 --> 01:13:06,510
又有件麻烦事
There's been another screwup.

1381
01:13:06,560 --> 01:13:08,040
洛马尼茨被军队征召了
Lomanitz just got drafted.

1382
01:13:08,320 --> 01:13:09,820
我们正在打仗  博士
We are at war, Doctor.

1383
01:13:09,820 --> 01:13:11,020
别犯浑  尼科斯
Don't be an asshole, Nichols.

1384
01:13:11,030 --> 01:13:13,130
我们需要这孩子  把这件事解决了  行吗
We need this kid. Fix it, will you?

1385
01:13:13,430 --> 01:13:14,470
这事本就没搞错
It wasn't a mistake.

1386
01:13:14,470 --> 01:13:17,610
你的朋友洛马尼茨一直试图成立放射性实验室工会
Your friend Lomanitz has been trying to unionize the radiation lab.

1387
01:13:17,620 --> 01:13:20,630
-他保证过停下的  -但他没停
- He promised to quit all that. - Well, he hasn't.

1388
01:13:21,290 --> 01:13:22,860
伯克利的安全官员担心
The security officer at Berkeley is concerned

1389
01:13:22,860 --> 01:13:25,080
共党会通过那个工会渗入
about communist infiltration through that union,

1390
01:13:25,080 --> 01:13:27,930
-叫FA...  -FAECT
- the FA... - FAECT.

1391
01:13:30,720 --> 01:13:34,260
我下周过去的时候  我会...顺路去找他
While I'm there next week, I'll... drop in to see him.

1392
01:13:36,360 --> 01:13:37,890
你的安全许可证下来了
Your Q clearance came through.

1393
01:13:41,580 --> 01:13:42,070
重要的是
It's important

1394
01:13:42,070 --> 01:13:45,100
你不要再和一些可疑的人有牵连
you not maintain or renew any questionable associations.

1395
01:13:50,240 --> 01:13:52,220
博士  你当时是否认为
Doctor, did you think social contacts

1396
01:13:52,220 --> 01:13:55,150
你作为接触战争机密的人
between a person engaged on secret war work

1397
01:13:55,170 --> 01:13:56,680
与共产党人接触很危险
and communists was dangerous?

1398
01:13:56,680 --> 01:13:59,540
今时今日我对这种危险有了更深刻的认知
My awareness of the danger would be greater today.

1399
01:14:00,740 --> 01:14:03,200
那就是说  可以说在战争时期
I mean, it's fair to say that during the war years,

1400
01:14:03,340 --> 01:14:06,380
你觉得此类接触是有潜在危险的
you felt that such contacts were potentially dangerous.

1401
01:14:12,990 --> 01:14:15,110
可以想见是危险的  没错
Were conceivably dangerous, yes.

1402
01:14:15,540 --> 01:14:16,990
说真的
I mean, really!

1403
01:14:18,060 --> 01:14:19,370
公开的共产党人
Known communists.

1404
01:14:22,330 --> 01:14:23,440
听着...
Look...

1405
01:14:24,730 --> 01:14:28,670
一直以来我的脑海里都有许多秘密
I've had a lot of secrets in my head for a long time.

1406
01:14:29,920 --> 01:14:34,290
无论我与谁交往  我都不会谈起这些秘密
Doesn't matter who I associate with, I don't talk about those secrets.

1407
01:14:41,880 --> 01:14:43,150
你在你的声明中说
You said in your statement

1408
01:14:44,410 --> 01:14:49,370
1943年你必须去见吉恩·塔特洛克
that you had to see Jean Tatlock in 1943.

1409
01:14:50,910 --> 01:14:52,110
你离开了
You left.

1410
01:14:53,650 --> 01:14:54,810
一句话都没留
Not a word.

1411
01:14:55,550 --> 01:14:57,360
你觉得我会怎么想
What did you think that would do to me?

1412
01:14:58,800 --> 01:14:59,910
我写过信
I wrote.

1413
01:15:00,180 --> 01:15:01,610
里面一句有用的都没有
Pages of nothing.

1414
01:15:04,580 --> 01:15:06,010
你去哪里了
Where did you go?

1415
01:15:07,960 --> 01:15:09,490
-我不能告诉你  -为什么
- I can't tell you. - Why not?

1416
01:15:09,540 --> 01:15:11,010
因为你是个共产党
Because you're a communist.

1417
01:15:13,890 --> 01:15:15,770
你为什么必须去见她
Why did you have to see her?

1418
01:15:15,940 --> 01:15:20,500
我们离开前  她表示极其想见我
She had indicated a great desire to see me before we left.

1419
01:15:20,500 --> 01:15:24,690
那时我没能去见她  但我觉得她必须见到我
At that time I couldn't, but I felt that she had to see me.

1420
01:15:25,480 --> 01:15:29,670
她当时正在接受精神治疗  她非常难过
She was undergoing psychiatric treatment. She was extremely unhappy.

1421
01:15:29,750 --> 01:15:32,200
你弄清楚她为什么必须见你了吗
Did you find out why she had to see you?

1422
01:15:37,360 --> 01:15:39,300
因为她依旧爱着我
Because she was still in love with me.

1423
01:15:46,940 --> 01:15:48,490
你们共度了一夜  是吗
You spent the night together, didn't you?

1424
01:15:56,520 --> 01:15:57,570
是的
Yes.

1425
01:16:04,200 --> 01:16:06,910
你在我的生命中出现又离开
You drop in and out of my life,

1426
01:16:07,120 --> 01:16:08,940
也不用和我解释为什么
and you don't have to tell me why.

1427
01:16:09,990 --> 01:16:12,830
-这就是所谓的掌控权  -我也不想这样
- And that's power. - Not that I enjoy.

1428
01:16:14,060 --> 01:16:16,570
我宁愿在你需要的时候陪着你
I'd rather be here for you as you need.

1429
01:16:16,770 --> 01:16:19,070
但你如今有了更重要的事
But you have other priorities now.

1430
01:16:19,730 --> 01:16:21,520
我有了妻子和孩子
I have a wife and child.

1431
01:16:22,660 --> 01:16:25,360
你我都心知肚明我们在说的不是这个
That's not what either of us is talking about.

1432
01:16:28,800 --> 01:16:32,390
吉恩...你要我过来
Jean... you asked me to come.

1433
01:16:33,480 --> 01:16:35,260
我也很高兴我来了
And I'm glad I did.

1434
01:16:36,080 --> 01:16:37,910
但我之后不能再见你了
But I can't see you again.

1435
01:16:41,000 --> 01:16:42,580
那如果我需要你怎么办
But what if I need you?

1436
01:16:46,500 --> 01:16:48,900
你说过你一定会接的
You said you would always answer.

1437
01:16:51,770 --> 01:16:52,980
不说话了吗
Not a word?

1438
01:16:54,360 --> 01:16:56,520
你当时认为这符合安全规定吗
Did you think that consistent with good security?

1439
01:16:56,520 --> 01:16:57,880
事实上  是符合的
As a matter of fact, it was.

1440
01:16:58,500 --> 01:16:59,540
我什么都没说
Not a word.

1441
01:17:00,760 --> 01:17:02,140
在此之后  你还在何时见过她
When did you see her after that?

1442
01:17:10,900 --> 01:17:12,370
再也没见过了
I never saw her again.

1443
01:17:18,900 --> 01:17:21,300
我还能赶上最后一班火车回普林斯顿
I can make the last train back to Princeton.

1444
01:17:22,200 --> 01:17:24,760
吉蒂  我刚刚说的话我之前全都告诉过你
Kitty, I didn't say anything that I hadn't already told you.

1445
01:17:24,760 --> 01:17:26,750
但今天你可是向全世界宣告了  不是吗
Today you said it to history, didn't you?

1446
01:17:26,760 --> 01:17:28,210
这是个闭门听证会
This is a closed hearing.

1447
01:17:30,310 --> 01:17:32,840
就算他们不公开笔录  我敢肯定你也会的
If they don't release the transcript, I'm sure you will.

1448
01:17:32,840 --> 01:17:35,120
-我宣誓过的  -你对我也曾宣誓过
- I was under oath. - Well, you were under an oath to me

1449
01:17:35,120 --> 01:17:36,500
但你还是去见吉恩了
when you went to see Jean.

1450
01:17:38,000 --> 01:17:39,200
你知道吗  你...
You know, you...

1451
01:17:40,310 --> 01:17:43,100
你坐在那里  日复一日
You sit there, day after day,

1452
01:17:43,810 --> 01:17:46,070
任由他们把我们的生活撕成碎片
letting them pick our lives to pieces.

1453
01:17:48,580 --> 01:17:49,970
你为什么不反抗
Why won't you fight?

1454
01:17:53,480 --> 01:17:56,370
罗伯特  我不会让她作证的
Robert, I'm not putting her up there.

1455
01:18:01,960 --> 01:18:04,910
奥本海默博士  真是荣幸  快请坐
Dr. Oppenheimer! This is an honor. Please, take a seat.

1456
01:18:04,910 --> 01:18:08,070
不用了  我只是来看看我是否应该...
No need. I just wanted to check whether I should...

1457
01:18:08,230 --> 01:18:09,440
趁着我在这里和洛马尼茨谈谈
talk to Lomanitz while I'm here,

1458
01:18:09,440 --> 01:18:10,780
毕竟你们有所顾虑
given your concerns.

1459
01:18:10,850 --> 01:18:12,430
我得说这其实取决于你  教授
I'd say that's really up to you, Professor,

1460
01:18:12,430 --> 01:18:13,800
但如果是我  我会谨慎一些
but I'd be cautious.

1461
01:18:14,110 --> 01:18:15,070
明白
Understood.

1462
01:18:15,260 --> 01:18:17,680
对了  说到工会
Oh, and, um, as regards to the union,

1463
01:18:17,680 --> 01:18:21,390
我想提醒你们留意一个叫埃尔滕顿的人
I wanted to give you a heads up on a man named Eltenton.

1464
01:18:21,390 --> 01:18:22,330
提醒
A heads up?

1465
01:18:22,330 --> 01:18:25,990
是的  也许他值得留意  仅此而已
Yes, just that he might bear watching, is all.

1466
01:18:27,310 --> 01:18:28,800
我很乐意听听细节
I'd love to get more details.

1467
01:18:29,840 --> 01:18:32,250
我现在有安排  而且明天一早就要离开
I have an appointment now, and I leave early tomorrow.

1468
01:18:32,270 --> 01:18:33,880
明天您多早来都可以
Well, come back as early as you like.

1469
01:18:34,360 --> 01:18:35,710
既然您现在没空
Since you haven't time now.

1470
01:18:36,990 --> 01:18:38,510
你第二天早上过去了
You went back the next morning.

1471
01:18:38,650 --> 01:18:40,570
是的  我不得不去
I did. I had to, really.

1472
01:18:41,660 --> 01:18:43,110
这次在场的还有另一个人
This time there was another man.

1473
01:18:45,120 --> 01:18:46,540
他说他姓帕什
He said his name was Pash.

1474
01:18:46,650 --> 01:18:49,040
帕什  你见到了帕什上校
Pash. You met Colonel Pash?

1475
01:18:49,110 --> 01:18:49,770
帕什上校
Colonel Pash,

1476
01:18:49,770 --> 01:18:54,370
你能读一下你1943年6月29日的备忘录吗
could you please read from your memo dated June 29, 1943?

1477
01:18:56,380 --> 01:18:58,690
"对该对象的监视结果显示
"Results of surveillance conducted on subject

1478
01:18:58,690 --> 01:19:01,650
其可能存在的与共产党的联系
"indicate further possible Communist Party connections."

1479
01:19:01,650 --> 01:19:03,870
该对象面见了一个叫吉恩·塔特洛克的共产党
"Subject met with and spent considerable time

1480
01:19:03,870 --> 01:19:06,070
并与之共度了很长一段时间
"with one Jean Tatlock, a communist,

1481
01:19:06,070 --> 01:19:07,530
关于她的信息已附上"
"the record of whom is attached."

1482
01:19:07,540 --> 01:19:10,170
-对象指的是奥本海默博士吗  -是的
- The subject being Dr. Oppenheimer? - Yes.

1483
01:19:10,190 --> 01:19:11,820
你当时甚至还没见过他是吗
Whom you had not met?

1484
01:19:11,820 --> 01:19:13,320
当时没有  但不久之后就见到了
Not then, but soon after.

1485
01:19:13,320 --> 01:19:15,970
他是项目的安全主管  我不应该认识他吗
He's the head of security for the project. Shouldn't I know him?

1486
01:19:15,980 --> 01:19:17,400
不  他应该认识你
No, he should know you.

1487
01:19:18,280 --> 01:19:19,900
要我说我是绝不会让你和帕什共处一室的
I would never put you in a room with Pash.

1488
01:19:19,900 --> 01:19:20,790
为什么
Why not?

1489
01:19:20,970 --> 01:19:22,960
帕什第一次听说洛马尼茨的事时
When Pash first heard about Lomanitz,

1490
01:19:23,080 --> 01:19:26,030
他告诉联调局他打算绑架他
he told the FBI he was going to kidnap him,

1491
01:19:26,050 --> 01:19:27,400
把他带到一艘船上
take him out on a boat,

1492
01:19:27,810 --> 01:19:30,360
用苏联人的方式拷问他
and interrogate him in the Russian manner.

1493
01:19:33,310 --> 01:19:35,680
格罗夫斯将军交给了我一项任务
General Groves has placed in me a certain responsibility,

1494
01:19:35,680 --> 01:19:37,780
感觉就像是我有一个孩子但不能见他
and it's like having a child who I can't see,

1495
01:19:38,800 --> 01:19:40,060
只能遥控指挥
by remote control.

1496
01:19:41,460 --> 01:19:43,040
所以见到您本人真是...
So to actually meet you is...

1497
01:19:44,760 --> 01:19:46,900
-我不会占用您太多时间  -不不
- I won't take up too much of your time. - Oh, no.

1498
01:19:47,060 --> 01:19:48,490
完全不会  任何时间都可以
Not at all. Whatever time you choose.

1499
01:19:49,550 --> 01:19:51,940
约翰逊先生和我说了你俩昨天的对话
Mr. Johnson told me of the conversation you had yesterday,

1500
01:19:51,940 --> 01:19:54,610
我对此非常感兴趣  也担心了一整天
which I'm very interested in. It's had me worried all day.

1501
01:19:55,460 --> 01:19:57,740
是的  我不想在没得到许可的情况下
Yes, well, I didn't want to talk to Lomanitz

1502
01:19:57,740 --> 01:19:59,030
和洛马尼茨交谈
without authorization.

1503
01:19:59,040 --> 01:20:00,990
我感兴趣的不是这件事
That's not the particular interest that I have.

1504
01:20:00,990 --> 01:20:02,640
而是一件更加...
It's something a little bit more...

1505
01:20:04,200 --> 01:20:05,590
在我看来  更加严重的事
In my opinion, more serious.

1506
01:20:05,590 --> 01:20:06,920
然后当联调局指出
And then when the FBI pointed out

1507
01:20:06,930 --> 01:20:09,880
这样得来的信息法庭不会接受时
that such information wouldn't be admissible in court,

1508
01:20:09,880 --> 01:20:11,560
帕什清楚地表明
Pash made it clear he had no intention

1509
01:20:11,570 --> 01:20:14,070
任何可以指控他的证人  他都不会留活口
of leaving any witness left to prosecute.

1510
01:20:14,170 --> 01:20:15,490
幸好联调局打消了他这个念头
Now, the FBI talked him down,

1511
01:20:15,490 --> 01:20:17,450
但你要对付的就是这种人
but that's the man you're dancing with.

1512
01:20:17,510 --> 01:20:20,040
我了解到你听说有其他势力
I gather you've heard there are other parties

1513
01:20:20,040 --> 01:20:22,050
对放射性实验室的工作感兴趣
interested in the work of the radiation lab?

1514
01:20:23,200 --> 01:20:27,560
一名认识苏联领事的人
A man attached to the Soviet consul indicated,

1515
01:20:27,720 --> 01:20:31,410
通过中间人向该项目的成员表示
through intermediate people, to people on this project,

1516
01:20:31,420 --> 01:20:34,640
他愿意传递信息
that he was in a position to transmit information.

1517
01:20:34,680 --> 01:20:37,290
项目里怎么会有人想要这么做呢
Well, why would anyone on the project want to do that?

1518
01:20:39,110 --> 01:20:41,630
老实说  我明白也许有人认为
Frankly, I can see that there might be an argument

1519
01:20:41,630 --> 01:20:43,670
总司令应该与苏联通气
for the commander-in-Chief informing the Russians,

1520
01:20:43,670 --> 01:20:46,170
毕竟他们是我们的盟友  但是...
they're our allies, after all, but...

1521
01:20:46,180 --> 01:20:48,660
我不喜欢偷偷摸摸这么做
I don't like the idea of it going out the back door.

1522
01:20:48,840 --> 01:20:51,240
留意一下这件事也许没什么坏处
It might not hurt to be on the lookout for it.

1523
01:20:52,540 --> 01:20:53,870
你是这么和帕什说的
And you said that to Pash.

1524
01:20:54,180 --> 01:20:58,460
我是试图说明"苏联不是德国"
I was trying to put it in the context of "Russia's not Germany".

1525
01:20:58,720 --> 01:21:03,060
鲍里斯·帕什的父亲是一名东正教主教
Boris Pash is the son of a Russian Orthodox bishop.

1526
01:21:03,060 --> 01:21:04,110
他出生在美国
Born here,

1527
01:21:04,130 --> 01:21:07,510
但1918年回了苏俄与布尔什维克作战
but in 1918 he went back to Russia to fight the Bolsheviks.

1528
01:21:07,640 --> 01:21:10,460
这是一个亲手杀过共产党的人
This is a man who has killed communists with his own hands.

1529
01:21:10,940 --> 01:21:13,400
谁该不该得到信息这件事不由我评判
I'm not the judge of who should or should not have information.

1530
01:21:13,610 --> 01:21:16,160
我的职责是阻止信息非法泄露
It's my business to stop it from going through illegally.

1531
01:21:16,420 --> 01:21:18,060
您能说得更详细些吗
Could you be a little more specific?

1532
01:21:20,930 --> 01:21:24,840
有个人的名字我听过几次
There's a man whose name was mentioned to me, a couple of times,

1533
01:21:24,840 --> 01:21:25,900
埃尔滕顿
Eltenton.

1534
01:21:27,190 --> 01:21:29,730
他应该是壳牌公司的一名化学家
I believe he's a chemist who works at Shell.

1535
01:21:30,280 --> 01:21:33,280
他与他的一个朋友交流过
He talked to a friend of his,

1536
01:21:33,280 --> 01:21:36,100
这位朋友是项目里某人的熟人
who's an acquaintance of someone on the project.

1537
01:21:38,240 --> 01:21:40,390
然后你以为你说到这个程度  帕什就满足了
And you thought Pash would be satisfied with that?

1538
01:21:40,390 --> 01:21:42,780
我本意是把埃尔滕顿给他们
I was attempting to give them Eltenton

1539
01:21:42,780 --> 01:21:44,130
但又不引起更大的麻烦
without opening a can of worms.

1540
01:21:44,130 --> 01:21:45,940
我给他们编了个故事
I told them a cock-and-bull story.

1541
01:21:46,100 --> 01:21:48,530
-你当时对格罗夫斯将军也撒谎了吗  -没有
- Did you lie to General Groves, too? - No.

1542
01:21:48,660 --> 01:21:51,340
我向他坦白  我对帕什撒谎了
I admitted to him that I'd lied to Pash.

1543
01:21:51,340 --> 01:21:54,450
你还记得关于薛瓦利埃事件的那次谈话吗
Do you recall this conversation about the Chevalier incident?

1544
01:21:55,210 --> 01:21:57,420
我见过许多不同的版本...
I've seen so many versions of it, uh...

1545
01:21:57,720 --> 01:22:00,610
之前我并不迷惑  但如今显然开始迷惑了
Wasn't confused before, but I'm certainly getting there now.

1546
01:22:00,670 --> 01:22:03,500
-那么你的结论是什么  -他受到了典型的
- And what was your conclusion? - That he was under the influence

1547
01:22:03,500 --> 01:22:06,950
美式校园男生小团体思维的影响
of the typical American schoolboy attitude

1548
01:22:06,950 --> 01:22:10,390
觉得自己不能告发朋友
that there's something wicked about telling on a friend.

1549
01:22:10,540 --> 01:22:14,780
那么  能告诉我这个中间人是谁吗
Well now, might we know through whom the contact was made?

1550
01:22:15,540 --> 01:22:19,430
这会牵扯到和此事无关的人
That would involve people who are not to be involved in this.

1551
01:22:19,460 --> 01:22:22,310
这个人是计划里的一员吗
Is that someone a member of the project?

1552
01:22:22,880 --> 01:22:26,350
是教职人员  但没参与计划
A member of the faculty, yes, but not in the project, no.

1553
01:22:27,970 --> 01:22:29,900
所以埃尔滕顿
So Eltenton made his approach

1554
01:22:29,910 --> 01:22:32,300
通过伯克利的某个教职人员接触到了计划
through a member of the faculty here at Berkeley.

1555
01:22:34,550 --> 01:22:37,000
据我所知  是的
As far as I know, as far as I know, yes.

1556
01:22:37,000 --> 01:22:41,620
但可能  牵扯到不止一个人
But there... may have been... more than one person involved.

1557
01:22:46,590 --> 01:22:49,360
先生们  如果我...看起来不太配合
Gentlemen, if I... if I seem uncooperative,

1558
01:22:49,370 --> 01:22:52,040
我希望你们理解  因为我坚持
I think you can understand it's because of my insistence

1559
