01:31:50,230 --> 01:31:52,650
只需要通过对核能的国际管控
Simply by limiting the spread of atomic weapons

1723
01:31:52,650 --> 01:31:55,100
限制核武器的扩散
through international control on nuclear energy.

1724
01:31:55,860 --> 01:31:57,740
你是指世界政府
By which you mean world government.

1725
01:31:57,740 --> 01:32:00,370
联合国  正如罗斯福所设想
The United Nations, as Roosevelt intended.

1726
01:32:00,370 --> 01:32:04,250
我问的是杜鲁门该怎么做  好吗  世界已经变了
Well, I asked what Truman should do, right? The world's changed.

1727
01:32:04,250 --> 01:32:08,120
现在威胁我们生存的不是法西斯主义而是共产主义
It's not fascism but communism that now threatens our survival.

1728
01:32:08,130 --> 01:32:11,670
路易斯  你是否明白  如果我们造了氢弹
Lewis, do you understand, if we build a hydrogen bomb,

1729
01:32:11,670 --> 01:32:14,010
苏联人也不得不造他们自己的
the Russians will have no choice but to build their own?

1730
01:32:14,010 --> 01:32:15,880
他们有没有可能已经在造了
Could they be working on one already?

1731
01:32:15,930 --> 01:32:18,640
基于间谍从洛斯阿拉莫斯收集的情报
Based on information gathered from the spy at Los Alamos...

1732
01:32:18,640 --> 01:32:20,220
-洛斯阿拉莫斯没有间谍  -先生们
- No spy at Los Alamos. - Gentlemen...

1733
01:32:20,220 --> 01:32:22,630
-没有吗  -我们别偏题
- There wasn't? - Let's not get sidetracked.

1734
01:32:23,140 --> 01:32:25,810
我是说我们要通过承诺不造氢弹
I say we use this moment to gain concessions from the Russians

1735
01:32:25,810 --> 01:32:28,900
来获得苏联人的让步
by committing that we will not build a hydrogen bomb.

1736
01:32:28,900 --> 01:32:30,730
这样会透露氢弹是存在的
Thereby revealing its existence.

1737
01:32:30,730 --> 01:32:32,810
你似乎很确信他们已经知道了
Which you seem convinced they already know.

1738
01:32:32,820 --> 01:32:33,560
好了
Alright.

1739
01:32:34,070 --> 01:32:37,700
现在我希望委员会成员私下会面
At this point, I'd like the committee members to meet in privacy

1740
01:32:37,700 --> 01:32:39,980
敲定我们的提议
to finalize our recommendations.

1741
01:32:41,240 --> 01:32:43,540
我只是不确定你想要走上这条路
I'm just not sure you want to go down this route.

1742
01:32:43,540 --> 01:32:45,790
路易斯  不是不尊重  我们是咨询委员会
Lewis, with respect, we are the advisory committee.

1743
01:32:45,790 --> 01:32:47,240
我们应该给出我们的意见
We will give them our advice.

1744
01:32:47,790 --> 01:32:48,490
晚安
Good night.

1745
01:32:52,920 --> 01:32:55,120
奥本海默博士  您好
Dr. Oppenheimer? Hi.

1746
01:32:55,470 --> 01:32:58,300
威廉·波登  国会原子能联合委员会的
William Borden. Joint Committee on Atomic Energy.

1747
01:32:58,300 --> 01:32:59,790
是的  是的
Oh, yes, yes.

1748
01:32:59,800 --> 01:33:01,130
战争期间  我是一名飞行员
During the war, I was a pilot.

1749
01:33:02,560 --> 01:33:07,230
有一天夜里  我突袭回来  看到了惊人的一幕
One night, flying back from a raid, I saw an amazing sight.

1750
01:33:07,230 --> 01:33:11,060
像流星一样  一枚V2火箭冲向英国
Like a meteor. A V2 rocket headed to England.

1751
01:33:11,730 --> 01:33:13,820
我忍不住想象
I can't help but imagine what it will be

1752
01:33:13,820 --> 01:33:18,150
这样的敌军火箭载着核弹头会是什么样
for such an enemy rocket to carry an atomic warhead.

1753
01:33:27,120 --> 01:33:29,410
我们要确保这种情况不会发生
Let's make sure we're not the ones to make that possible.

1754
01:33:35,920 --> 01:33:38,370
奥比  你应该不想和施特劳斯作对吧
Oppie, I don't think you want to go up against Strauss.

1755
01:33:38,800 --> 01:33:41,210
如果我俩都发言  其他人会听我的
If we both speak, they listen to me.

1756
01:33:41,640 --> 01:33:43,510
他们听你说话像先知
When you speak, they hear a prophet.

1757
01:33:43,510 --> 01:33:45,680
他们听施特劳斯说话才像常人
When Strauss speaks, they hear themselves.

1758
01:33:45,680 --> 01:33:47,010
他们会听先知的
They'll listen to a prophet.

1759
01:33:47,640 --> 01:33:50,720
先知不能出错  一次都不行
A prophet can't be wrong. Not once.

1760
01:33:50,900 --> 01:33:52,020
你是否指责过奥本海默
Did you accuse Oppenheimer

1761
01:33:52,020 --> 01:33:54,190
蓄意破坏了氢弹的研发
of sabotaging the development of the Super?

1762
01:33:54,190 --> 01:33:58,480
我从来不会滥用"蓄意破坏"这类词
I was never one of those to bandy around terms like sabotage.

1763
01:33:58,780 --> 01:34:00,150
但波登先生会
But Mr. Borden was?

1764
01:34:00,780 --> 01:34:02,400
据我的理解  有可能
As I understand it, possibly.

1765
01:34:02,450 --> 01:34:06,200
波登先生是如何整理出一份如此详尽的起诉书的
How was Mr. Borden able to put together such a detailed indictment?

1766
01:34:06,200 --> 01:34:07,830
他当时已不是政府雇员
He was no longer a government employee,

1767
01:34:07,830 --> 01:34:10,210
但他似乎可以不受任何限制地
yet he appears to have had unlimited access

1768
01:34:10,210 --> 01:34:11,870
查阅奥本海默博士的档案
to Dr. Oppenheimer's file.

1769
01:34:11,870 --> 01:34:14,460
有可能是尼科斯先生把这些文件给他的吗
Might Mr. Nichols have given him access to the file?

1770
01:34:14,460 --> 01:34:16,960
还是原子能委员会的某个人
Or someone else at the AEC?

1771
01:34:16,960 --> 01:34:18,910
这是一个非常严重的指控  参议员
That's a very serious accusation, Senator.

1772
01:34:19,590 --> 01:34:20,970
你是不是在暗示
Is it your intention to suggest that

1773
01:34:20,970 --> 01:34:24,040
奥本海默博士背叛了美国
Dr. Oppenheimer is disloyal to the United States?

1774
01:34:24,430 --> 01:34:26,680
我一直认为  到现在仍然认为
I've always assumed, and still assume,

1775
01:34:26,680 --> 01:34:28,550
他忠于美国
that he's loyal to the United States.

1776
01:34:29,060 --> 01:34:30,930
我坚信  也会继续坚信这一点
I believe this, and I shall believe it,

1777
01:34:30,940 --> 01:34:33,600
除非我看到非常确凿的反驳证据
until I see very conclusive proof to the opposite.

1778
01:34:33,810 --> 01:34:37,890
你认为奥本海默博士是安全风险吗
Do you or do you not believe that Dr. Oppenheimer is a security risk?

1779
01:34:46,700 --> 01:34:49,700
恕我直言  希特勒在地堡里举枪自尽后
If I may, look, when Hitler blew his brains out in that bunker,

1780
01:34:49,700 --> 01:34:52,120
我认为这枚炸弹
it is my humble opinion that there is no need

1781
01:34:52,120 --> 01:34:54,950
就没必要再离开这个试验场地了
for that bomb to be seen anywhere except that test site.

1782
01:34:55,880 --> 01:34:57,920
我们至少应该停下来思考一下
Well, we at least have to take a moment to think about

1783
01:34:57,920 --> 01:35:01,370
手段是否还能证明目的的正当性  因为...
whether the means justify the ends any longer because...

1784
01:35:04,090 --> 01:35:06,670
德国就快投降了
Germany is about to surrender.

1785
01:35:08,470 --> 01:35:12,560
敌人不再是对人类最大的威胁
It's no longer the enemy who are the greatest threat to mankind.

1786
01:35:12,560 --> 01:35:13,760
我们的工作才是
It's our work.

1787
01:35:16,110 --> 01:35:18,720
希特勒死了  没错
Hitler's dead. It's true.

1788
01:35:20,440 --> 01:35:22,020
但日本人还在顽抗
But the Japanese fight on.

1789
01:35:22,320 --> 01:35:23,980
他们的战败似乎已成定局
Their defeat seems assured.

1790
01:35:24,240 --> 01:35:26,480
正要奔赴前线的大兵可不会这么认为
Not if you're a G.I. preparing to invade.

1791
01:35:27,990 --> 01:35:29,330
我们可以结束这场战争
We can end this war.

1792
01:35:29,330 --> 01:35:30,790
但要如何才能证明
But how do we justify

1793
01:35:30,790 --> 01:35:32,610
对人类使用这种武器是合乎道义的
using this weapon on human beings?

1794
01:35:35,960 --> 01:35:39,040
我们研究的是理论  对吧
We're theorists. Yes?

1795
01:35:40,170 --> 01:35:44,960
我们想象未来  但这一想象让我们恐惧
We imagine a future, and our imaginings horrify us.

1796
01:35:45,640 --> 01:35:47,970
他们只有理解了才会害怕
They won't fear it until they understand it,

1797
01:35:47,970 --> 01:35:50,510
而他们只有用过才能理解
and they won't understand it until they've used it.

1798
01:35:50,770 --> 01:35:54,380
洛斯阿拉莫斯的可怕秘密公诸于世后
When the world learns the terrible secret of Los Alamos,

1799
01:35:54,770 --> 01:35:58,310
我们在这里的工作将确保人类前所未有的和平
our work here will ensure a peace mankind has never seen.

1800
01:35:58,310 --> 01:36:01,360
这种建立在国际合作上的和平
A peace based on the kind of international cooperation

1801
01:36:01,360 --> 01:36:03,770
正是罗斯福一直设想的
that Roosevelt always envisaged.

1802
01:36:08,740 --> 01:36:11,780
-进展如何  -两年时间  花费十亿美元
- Progress? - Two years and a billion dollars' worth.

1803
01:36:12,910 --> 01:36:15,960
-难以估价  -不难  把账单加起来就知道了
- Hard to put a price on it. - Not really, just add up the bills.

1804
01:36:15,960 --> 01:36:17,880
农村免费包裹投递[接生]Rural free deliveries.

1805
01:36:17,880 --> 01:36:19,990
第一年就降生了80个新生儿
80 babies delivered the first year.

1806
01:36:20,380 --> 01:36:22,450
今年一个月就多出了10个孩子
This year we've had ten, a month.

1807
01:36:23,010 --> 01:36:25,870
节育问题有点超出我的管辖范围了  将军
Birth control is a little out of my jurisdiction, General.

1808
01:36:26,590 --> 01:36:28,000
-很明显  -将军
- Clearly. - General.

1809
01:36:33,430 --> 01:36:36,760
趴下  各位  福克斯  趴下
Head down, everybody. Fuchs, head down.

1810
01:36:44,240 --> 01:36:45,270
就是这样
That's the one!

1811
01:36:45,610 --> 01:36:47,100
两枚可引爆的炸弹
Two viable bombs.

1812
01:36:47,280 --> 01:36:48,150
我需要一个日期
I need a date.

1813
01:36:51,080 --> 01:36:51,980
九月
September.

1814
01:36:52,450 --> 01:36:53,440
七月
July.

1815
01:36:53,870 --> 01:36:55,450
大获成功  先生们
That's the sweet spot, gentlemen.

1816
01:36:56,160 --> 01:36:57,030
八月
August.

1817
01:36:57,870 --> 01:36:58,740
七月
July.

1818
01:36:59,420 --> 01:37:00,700
七月试爆
Tests in July.

1819
01:37:01,420 --> 01:37:02,660
但我需要我弟弟
But I need my brother.

1820
01:37:07,010 --> 01:37:09,430
弗兰克了解这片沙漠  他已经放下政治了
Frank knows the desert. He's left politics behind.

1821
01:37:09,430 --> 01:37:11,550
他已经和劳伦斯共事两年了
He's been working with Lawrence for two years now.

1822
01:37:18,770 --> 01:37:20,100
试验要叫什么
What do we call the test?

1823
01:37:22,020 --> 01:37:25,430
"猛击我的心吧  三位一体的上帝"[约翰·邓恩《圣十四行诗》]"Batter my heart, three-person'd God."

1824
01:37:25,440 --> 01:37:26,350
什么
What?

1825
01:37:28,240 --> 01:37:29,400
三位一体
Trinity.

1826
01:37:37,120 --> 01:37:39,290
你坚持要让你的弟弟弗兰克加入
You insisted on bringing on your brother Frank,

1827
01:37:39,290 --> 01:37:40,460
一个知名的共产党
a known communist.

1828
01:37:40,460 --> 01:37:41,620
前共党
Former communist.

1829
01:37:42,250 --> 01:37:44,290
你将一个知名的前共党...
You brought a known former communist...

1830
01:37:44,710 --> 01:37:48,050
引入了美国最机密也最重要的国防项目
onto America's most secret and important defense project.

1831
01:37:48,050 --> 01:37:51,000
我知道我的弟弟可以被信任  毋庸置疑
I knew my brother could be trusted. Absolutely.

1832
01:37:51,430 --> 01:37:52,840
你认为自己对团队中谁可以信任的判断
And you thought your judgment was sound

1833
01:37:52,850 --> 01:37:54,760
是正确的吗
on who on the team could be trusted?

1834
01:37:55,260 --> 01:37:56,550
福克斯  低头
Fuchs, head down.

1835
01:37:57,020 --> 01:37:58,590
好的  准备好了吗
Okay. Everybody ready?

1836
01:38:08,240 --> 01:38:09,570
希望你们有收获
I hope you learned something.

1837
01:38:09,570 --> 01:38:11,660
是的  知道了下次的安全距离要远得多
Yeah, we've learned we're gonna need to be a lot further away.

1838
01:38:11,660 --> 01:38:13,360
快点搞清楚
Well, figure it out, fast.

1839
01:38:13,370 --> 01:38:14,820
明天一早我们就去华盛顿
We leave for Washington in the morning.

1840
01:38:14,830 --> 01:38:16,070
要给他一个日期
We're going to give him a date.

1841
01:38:31,590 --> 01:38:33,390
这么大老远从芝加哥过来  利奥
You're a long way from Chicago, Leo.

1842
01:38:33,390 --> 01:38:36,670
我们再不采取行动  他们就要拿这个对付日本了
If we don't act now, they're going to use this thing against Japan.

1843
01:38:36,850 --> 01:38:39,420
我们预约了和杜鲁门会面  但被谁取消了
We booked a meeting with Truman, but somebody killed it.

1844
01:38:40,020 --> 01:38:42,270
你要去见战争部长
You're meeting the Secretary of War.

1845
01:38:42,270 --> 01:38:44,010
我们在造原子弹
Just because we're building it,

1846
01:38:44,060 --> 01:38:46,140
并不代表我们能决定怎么用
doesn't mean we get to decide how it's used.

1847
01:38:46,730 --> 01:38:48,390
历史会评判我们的  罗伯特
History will judge us, Robert.

1848
01:38:49,690 --> 01:38:51,560
我们在芝加哥起草了一份请愿书
In Chicago, we put together a petition.

1849
01:38:52,410 --> 01:38:54,400
我不...  我不要参与这事
I'm not... I'm not getting into this.

1850
01:38:59,370 --> 01:39:01,040
告诉我你的顾虑  我会传达
Just tell me your concerns, and I'll relate them.

1851
01:39:01,040 --> 01:39:03,950
我的顾虑  德国已经战败
My concerns? Germany's defeated.

1852
01:39:04,250 --> 01:39:05,710
日本独木难支
Japan's not going to hold out alone.

1853
01:39:05,710 --> 01:39:08,250
你怎么知道  是你把我们卷入这一切的
How could you know that? You got us into this.

1854
01:39:08,300 --> 01:39:08,960
你和爱因斯坦
You and Einstein,

1855
01:39:08,960 --> 01:39:11,300
写信给罗斯福说我们可以造一个炸弹
with your letter to Roosevelt saying we could build a bomb.

1856
01:39:11,300 --> 01:39:12,420
为了对抗德国
Against Germany.

1857
01:39:12,430 --> 01:39:15,430
武器制造不是这么简单的  西拉德
That's not how weapons manufacture works, Szilard.

1858
01:39:15,430 --> 01:39:16,760
奥比  你必须帮忙
Oppie, you have to help.

1859
01:39:16,760 --> 01:39:18,470
费米会出席会议  劳伦斯也会出席
Fermi's in the meeting. Lawrence is in the meeting.

1860
01:39:18,470 --> 01:39:21,720
他们不是你  你是科学界最厉害的推销员
They're not you. You're the great salesman of science.

1861
01:39:21,850 --> 01:39:24,140
你可以说服任何人
You can convince anyone of anything.

1862
01:39:25,270 --> 01:39:26,600
甚至你自己
Even yourself.

1863
01:39:27,320 --> 01:39:28,180
失陪了
Excuse me.

1864
01:39:29,480 --> 01:39:34,190
东京的大火造成十万人死亡  其中大部分是平民
The firestorm in Tokyo killed 100,000 people, mostly civilians.

1865
01:39:35,490 --> 01:39:38,780
我们做出这种事却没人抗议  让我很担心美国
I worry about America when we do these things and no one protests.

1866
01:39:38,910 --> 01:39:39,580
珍珠港事件
Pearl Harbor,

1867
01:39:39,580 --> 01:39:42,330
再加上太平洋地区持续三年的血战
and three years of brutal conflict in the Pacific,

1868
01:39:42,330 --> 01:39:44,950
极大地提高了美国民众的容忍度
buys a lot of latitude with the American public.

1869
01:39:45,080 --> 01:39:46,950
高到可以容忍投放原子弹吗
Enough to unleash the atomic bomb?

1870
01:39:47,250 --> 01:39:50,580
原子弹造成的破坏可能不会像东京轰炸那么严重
Uh, the A-bomb might not cause as much damage as the Tokyo bombings.

1871
01:39:50,800 --> 01:39:52,050
预估的数字呢
What are we estimating?

1872
01:39:52,050 --> 01:39:53,870
在一个中型城市
In a medium-sized city, uh...

1873
01:39:54,720 --> 01:39:56,930
两万到三万死亡
20,000 or 30,000 dead.

1874
01:39:56,930 --> 01:39:59,100
没错  但也不要低估
Yes, but don't underestimate

1875
01:39:59,100 --> 01:40:02,920
原子弹爆炸带来的心理冲击
the psychological impact of an atomic explosion.

1876
01:40:03,230 --> 01:40:06,600
三千米高的火柱
A pillar of fire, 10,000 feet tall,

1877
01:40:07,060 --> 01:40:10,480
方圆上下1.6千米的致命中子辐射效应
deadly neutron effects for a mile, in all directions,

1878
01:40:10,480 --> 01:40:13,320
仅通过一个装置
from one single device.

1879
01:40:13,320 --> 01:40:15,320
从一架隐蔽的B-29轰炸机上
Dropped from a barely-noticed B-29,

1880
01:40:15,320 --> 01:40:17,060
投下的原子弹将会是...
the atomic bomb will be...

1881
01:40:17,950 --> 01:40:20,820
神力的骇人展示
a terrible revelation of divine power.

1882
01:40:21,330 --> 01:40:23,780
果真如此的话  这将是决定性的一击
If that's true, it would be definitive.

1883
01:40:24,080 --> 01:40:25,780
二战将会结束
World War II would be over.

1884
01:40:26,080 --> 01:40:27,620
我们的大兵也就可以回家了
Our boys would come home.

1885
01:40:27,920 --> 01:40:29,160
打击军事目标吗
Military targets?

1886
01:40:30,090 --> 01:40:32,290
但没有足够大的军事目标
But there aren't any big enough.

1887
01:40:32,380 --> 01:40:35,220
命脉军工厂怎么样
