02:21:30,310 --> 02:21:31,300
我和胡佛谈过了
I've talked it over with Hoover.

2415
02:21:31,300 --> 02:21:33,100
他会拖住麦卡锡
He'll hold McCarthy at bay

2416
02:21:33,100 --> 02:21:35,300
同时你去面对原子能委员会
while you do this with the AEC.

2417
02:21:35,430 --> 02:21:37,390
-搞成庭审吗  -不  不能搞庭审
- Trial? - No, no trial.

2418
02:21:37,390 --> 02:21:40,350
你不能给奥本海默发挥的机会
You can't give Oppenheimer a platform.

2419
02:21:40,400 --> 02:21:41,940
不能让他悲情殉道
You can't martyr him.

2420
02:21:42,360 --> 02:21:45,570
我们必须彻彻底底地让奥本海默信誉扫地
We need a systematic destruction of Oppenheimer's credibility,

2421
02:21:45,570 --> 02:21:49,610
这样他就再也不能插手国家安全事务
so he can never again speak on matters of national security.

2422
02:21:49,950 --> 02:21:51,070
然后呢
Then what?

2423
02:21:52,580 --> 02:21:56,110
找个破旧的小房间  远离公众的视野
A shabby little room. Far from the limelight.

2424
02:22:01,670 --> 02:22:03,710
一个简单的官僚程序
A simple bureaucratic procedure.

2425
02:22:03,710 --> 02:22:06,130
他的安全许可快要到期了
His Q clearance. It's up for renewal.

2426
02:22:06,130 --> 02:22:09,250
你把指控信发给联调局
You send your accusations to the FBI...

2427
02:22:11,220 --> 02:22:13,050
胡佛再转发给原子能委员会
Hoover sends them to the AEC.

2428
02:22:13,050 --> 02:22:14,630
你被迫行动
You're forced to act.

2429
02:22:14,850 --> 02:22:16,670
写一份诉状
You write up an indictment.

2430
02:22:16,970 --> 02:22:17,810
然后告诉奥本海默
You tell Oppenheimer

2431
02:22:17,810 --> 02:22:20,350
他的许可到期不续了
his security clearance is not being renewed.

2432
02:22:20,770 --> 02:22:22,560
但给他一次上诉的机会
But offer him the chance to appeal.

2433
02:22:22,560 --> 02:22:25,110
如你所见  罗伯特  这份文件还没被签署
As you can see, Robert, it's not yet signed.

2434
02:22:25,110 --> 02:22:27,230
-我能留着吗  -不行
- May I keep this? - No.

2435
02:22:27,530 --> 02:22:29,570
如果你选择上诉
If you do decide to appeal,

2436
02:22:29,570 --> 02:22:31,350
他们才必须给你一份复件
they'll have to send you a copy.

2437
02:22:31,490 --> 02:22:34,650
等他上诉  而且信我的  他肯定会
When he appeals, and trust me, he will,

2438
02:22:34,910 --> 02:22:36,490
我就指派一个委员会
I appoint a board.

2439
02:22:37,080 --> 02:22:39,410
其中当然会有律师
They will, of course, have counsel.

2440
02:22:39,750 --> 02:22:41,540
-检察官吗  -有  不叫检察官而已
- Prosecutor? - In all but name.

2441
02:22:41,540 --> 02:22:43,870
-是谁  -罗杰·罗伯
- Who? - Roger Robb.

2442
02:22:44,630 --> 02:22:47,880
罗伯将有权查阅奥本海默的档案
Robb will have security clearance to examine Oppenheimer's file.

2443
02:22:47,880 --> 02:22:51,130
格雷委员会也有  但奥本海默的律师没有
As will the Gray Board. Defense counsel will not.

2444
02:22:52,180 --> 02:22:53,420
闭门听证会
A closed hearing.

2445
02:22:53,510 --> 02:22:57,560
在你们对我的起诉书中提到的所谓审讯信息
The so-called interrogatory information in your indictment of me...

2446
02:22:57,560 --> 02:23:01,560
没有旁听席和记者  无需举证
No audience, no reporters, no burden of proof.

2447
02:23:01,560 --> 02:23:03,140
无需举证
No burden of proof?

2448
02:23:04,650 --> 02:23:06,020
我们不是来定他罪的
We're not convicting.

2449
02:23:07,610 --> 02:23:09,140
我们是要搞垮他
We're just denying.

2450
02:23:14,410 --> 02:23:16,650
你怎么说的来着
What is it you said?

2451
02:23:17,370 --> 02:23:20,820
这只是游戏规则而已
This is just how the game is played.

2452
02:23:21,330 --> 02:23:23,160
请恕我天真
Well, forgive my naivete.

2453
02:23:23,670 --> 02:23:27,750
愚夫走到明处就被吞噬
Amateurs seek the sun, get eaten.

2454
02:23:28,720 --> 02:23:32,010
智者待在暗处观兵不动
Power stays in the shadows.

2455
02:23:32,010 --> 02:23:34,800
但您这次已经不能藏身于暗处了
But, sir, you're... you're out of the shadows now.

2456
02:23:34,800 --> 02:23:37,380
没错  所以我们的计划必须成功
Yeah, that's why this has to work.

2457
02:23:39,810 --> 02:23:41,770
泰勒今早出庭
Teller's testifying this morning.

2458
02:23:41,770 --> 02:23:43,680
还算有利  然后呢
That'll help. And then...

2459
02:23:44,480 --> 02:23:45,690
希尔下午出庭
Hill is in the afternoon.

2460
02:23:45,690 --> 02:23:47,430
希尔也会对我们有利
Hill is gonna help us too.

2461
02:23:50,360 --> 02:23:53,310
如你所见  罗伯特  这份文件还没被签署
As you can see, Robert, it's not yet signed.

2462
02:23:53,660 --> 02:23:55,480
-我能留着吗  -不行
- May I keep this? - No.

2463
02:23:57,870 --> 02:23:59,740
如果你选择上诉
If you do decide to appeal,

2464
02:23:59,750 --> 02:24:02,740
他们才必须给你一份复件
then they'll have to send you a copy.

2465
02:24:06,250 --> 02:24:08,700
让我的司机送你  别和我客气
Take my car and driver, I insist.

2466
02:24:13,220 --> 02:24:15,300
我要咨询我的律师  路易斯
I'll have to consult my lawyers, Lewis.

2467
02:24:15,300 --> 02:24:18,050
没问题  但别太久
Of course. But don't take too long.

2468
02:24:18,050 --> 02:24:19,960
尼科斯那边我也拖不了太久
I can't keep Nichols at bay.

2469
02:24:26,270 --> 02:24:28,470
罗伯特  我很抱歉事情弄到这步田地
I'm sorry it's come to this, Robert.

2470
02:24:28,650 --> 02:24:29,810
本不该这样的
I think it's wrong.

2471
02:24:43,040 --> 02:24:44,370
尼科斯希望我上诉
Nichols wants me to fight,

2472
02:24:44,370 --> 02:24:46,410
这样他就能把一切记录在案
so he can get it all on the record.

2473
02:24:46,620 --> 02:24:48,420
施特劳斯想让我放弃上诉
Strauss wants me to walk away.

2474
02:24:48,420 --> 02:24:51,170
施特劳斯吃准了你不会上诉
Strauss knows that you can't do that.

2475
02:24:51,170 --> 02:24:53,420
料定你会接受指控
You'd be accepting the charges.

2476
02:24:53,840 --> 02:24:55,260
这样你就会丢掉工作
You'll lose your job.

2477
02:24:55,260 --> 02:24:58,380
名誉扫地  我们连房子都保不住了
You will lose your reputation. We'll lose our house.

2478
02:24:58,380 --> 02:25:00,170
罗伯特  我们必须抗争
Robert, we have to fight.

2479
02:25:03,270 --> 02:25:05,680
作为原子能委员会的律师  我不能为你辩护
As AEC counsel, I can't represent you.

2480
02:25:05,680 --> 02:25:07,380
我会找劳埃德·加里森
I'll call Lloyd Garrison.

2481
02:25:07,600 --> 02:25:08,810
他很出色
Oh, he's good.

2482
02:25:08,810 --> 02:25:09,440
是最出色的
The best,

2483
02:25:09,440 --> 02:25:12,310
但我还是要提醒你
but I have to warn you.

2484
02:25:13,610 --> 02:25:15,190
这不是公平斗争
This won't be a fair fight.

2485
02:25:15,780 --> 02:25:18,200
1943年  你与鲍里斯·帕什的谈话中
During your interview with Boris Pash in 1943,

2486
02:25:18,200 --> 02:25:19,910
是否提到过缩微胶卷
did you refer to microfilm?

2487
02:25:19,910 --> 02:25:23,120
-没有  -11号文件  第1页  第3段
- No. - Tab 11, page one, paragraph three.

2488
02:25:23,120 --> 02:25:24,790
你从没说过  "领事馆的人
You never said, "man of the consulate,

2489
02:25:24,790 --> 02:25:26,620
用缩微胶卷的行家"
expert in the use of microfilm"?

2490
02:25:26,620 --> 02:25:27,790
-抱歉  打断一下  -不
- I'm sorry, I'm sorry... - No.

2491
02:25:27,790 --> 02:25:29,920
我想知道罗伯先生引用的是哪份文件
I would like to know what document Mr. Robb is quoting from,

2492
02:25:29,920 --> 02:25:32,000
能不能也给我们一份复件
and if we might be furnished with a copy.

2493
02:25:32,010 --> 02:25:33,960
这是保密文件  加里森先生
The document is classified, Mr. Garrison.

2494
02:25:33,960 --> 02:25:36,260
我觉得我们应该用第一手信息
I think we should get back to firsthand information.

2495
02:25:36,260 --> 02:25:37,590
这就是第一手信息
This is firsthand.

2496
02:25:37,590 --> 02:25:39,000
怎么确认的  罗杰
How so, Roger?

2497
02:25:40,840 --> 02:25:42,750
那次谈话被录音了
There was a recording of the interview.

2498
02:25:47,230 --> 02:25:50,110
你让我的委托人冒着做伪证的风险事无巨细地回忆
You let my client sit here and potentially perjure himself,

2499
02:25:50,110 --> 02:25:52,480
但其实你手里一直有一份录音
and all this time, you had a recording?

2500
02:25:52,480 --> 02:25:55,320
没人强迫你的委托人歪曲自己以前的言论
Nobody told your client to misrepresent his former answers.

2501
02:25:55,320 --> 02:25:57,690
歪曲  那可是12年前说的话
Misrepresent? It was 12 years ago!

2502
02:25:57,700 --> 02:25:58,900
我们可以听听录音吗
Can we hear this recording?

2503
02:25:58,910 --> 02:26:00,490
你没有听录音的权限  加里森先生
You don't have the clearance, Mr. Garrison.

2504
02:26:00,490 --> 02:26:02,410
那你读出来  它不就被记录在案了吗
But you're reading it into the record!

2505
02:26:02,410 --> 02:26:03,370
我来  我来
Please, please.

2506
02:26:03,370 --> 02:26:07,320
请问我们的质询是要诱供还是找真相
Is this proceeding interested in entrapment or in truth?

2507
02:26:07,410 --> 02:26:10,280
如果是真相  那公开透明呢
If it's truth, where's the disclosure?

2508
02:26:10,460 --> 02:26:11,250
有证人吗
Where's the witness list?

2509
02:26:11,250 --> 02:26:14,090
加里森先生  你很清楚我们这不是在法庭
Mr. Garrison, this isn't a trial, as you are well aware.

2510
02:26:14,090 --> 02:26:16,000
检方举证原则当下不适用
Evidentiary rules do not apply.

2511
02:26:16,000 --> 02:26:18,050
我们面临的是国家安全问题
We are dealing with national security.

2512
02:26:18,050 --> 02:26:19,380
我知道  先生  但恕我直言
Yes, sir, with all due respect,

2513
02:26:19,380 --> 02:26:20,590
我还是不能理解
I fail to see

2514
02:26:20,590 --> 02:26:23,510
为什么国家安全可以绕开庭审流程
how national security prevents the prosecution

2515
02:26:23,510 --> 02:26:26,060
连一份证人名单都不提供
from providing us with a list of witnesses!

2516
02:26:23,720 --> 02:26:26,860
{\an8}也许我们该休会一下了
Perhaps we are in need of a brief recess.

2517
02:26:26,060 --> 02:26:28,350
先生们  我向你们保证
Gentlemen. You have my words.

2518
02:26:28,350 --> 02:26:31,100
如果你们说它是来自一份笔录  我接受
If you say they're from a transcript, then I'll accept it.

2519
02:26:31,100 --> 02:26:33,940
我都解释过了  那是我胡乱编造的
I've already explained I made up a cock-and-bull story.

2520
02:26:33,940 --> 02:26:37,030
胡乱编造的故事怎么可以这么详实
And why would anyone make up such an elaborate story?

2521
02:26:37,030 --> 02:26:38,640
因为我犯蠢了
Because I was an idiot.

2522
02:26:39,450 --> 02:26:40,690
为什么胡编
Why lie?

2523
02:26:40,780 --> 02:26:43,320
为的就是不把中间人
Well, clearly with the intention of not revealing

2524
02:26:43,320 --> 02:26:45,080
公之于众
who the intermediary was.

2525
02:26:45,080 --> 02:26:47,700
哈康·薛瓦利埃  你的那位共产党朋友
Your friend, Haakon Chevalier, the communist.

2526
02:26:47,830 --> 02:26:49,280
你们现在还是朋友么
Is he still your friend?

2527
02:26:49,830 --> 02:26:50,740
是
Yes.

2528
02:26:54,170 --> 02:26:56,330
拉比博士  感谢你能来
Dr. Rabi, thank you for coming.

2529
02:26:56,380 --> 02:26:58,420
你知道他们还传唤了谁吗
You know who else the prosecution has called?

2530
02:26:58,420 --> 02:27:00,580
泰勒  明摆着的
Teller, obviously.

2531
02:27:01,430 --> 02:27:02,790
他们肯定问了劳伦斯
They've asked Lawrence.

2532
02:27:02,840 --> 02:27:03,680
他怎么说的
What did he say?

2533
02:27:03,680 --> 02:27:05,550
他本来是想站在你这边的
He wasn't going to help them,

2534
02:27:05,760 --> 02:27:07,340
-但是  -但是什么
- but... - But?

2535
02:27:07,810 --> 02:27:08,940
施特劳斯告诉他
Strauss told him that

2536
02:27:08,940 --> 02:27:12,350
你和露丝·托尔曼有染好多年了
you and Ruth Tolman had been having an affair for years.

2537
02:27:12,350 --> 02:27:14,850
从你和他们一起住在帕萨迪纳时就开始了
The whole time you lived with them in Pasadena.

2538
02:27:15,020 --> 02:27:16,440
他让劳伦斯相信
He convinced Lawrence that

2539
02:27:16,440 --> 02:27:18,270
理查德就是因为这个伤心过世
Richard died of a broken heart.

2540
02:27:18,280 --> 02:27:20,320
-无稽之谈  -哪里无稽
- That's absurd. - What part?

2541
02:27:20,320 --> 02:27:21,650
伤心过世
A broken heart.

2542
02:27:22,150 --> 02:27:23,520
理查德根本就蒙在鼓里
Richard never found out.

2543
02:27:24,450 --> 02:27:26,070
劳伦斯也来作证吗
Is Lawrence gonna testify?

2544
02:27:26,200 --> 02:27:27,200
我不确定
I don't know.

2545
02:27:28,080 --> 02:27:32,580
拉比博士  你目前担任什么公职
Dr. Rabi, what governmental positions do you currently hold?

2546
02:27:32,710 --> 02:27:36,550
我接替了奥本海默博士
I am the chairman of the general advisory committee to the AEC,

2547
02:27:36,550 --> 02:27:38,550
担任原子能委员会的顾问委员会主席
succeeding Dr. Oppenheimer.

2548
02:27:38,550 --> 02:27:41,000
你和奥本海默博士相识多久了
And how long have you known Dr. Oppenheimer?

2549
02:27:41,510 --> 02:27:43,050
1928年认识的
Since 1928.

2550
02:27:43,050 --> 02:27:45,640
我对他十分了解
I... I know him quite well.

2551
02:27:45,640 --> 02:27:49,670
了解到足以评价他的人格品性吗
Well enough to speak to the bearing of his loyalty and character?

2552
02:27:49,890 --> 02:27:53,550
奥本海默博士品行正直
Dr. Oppenheimer is a man of upstanding character.

2553
02:27:53,980 --> 02:27:57,860
对于祖国和朋友  以及他的工作机构
And he is loyal to the United States, to his friends,

2554
02:27:57,860 --> 02:28:00,270
都无比的忠诚
to the institutions of which he is part.

2555
02:28:01,860 --> 02:28:02,690
吃吧
Eat.

2556
02:28:22,420 --> 02:28:23,290
刚才是谁
Who was that?

2557
02:28:23,470 --> 02:28:24,920
没谁  别担心
Nothing to worry about.

2558
02:28:28,140 --> 02:28:29,720
苏联人试爆了原子弹后
After the Russian A-bomb test,

2559
02:28:29,720 --> 02:28:32,270
劳伦斯博士找你讨论过氢弹的事吗
did Dr. Lawrence come to see you about the hydrogen bomb?

2560
02:28:32,270 --> 02:28:34,140
那你最好去问他
You'd be better off asking him.

2561
02:28:34,140 --> 02:28:35,720
我自然要问
Well, I fully intend to.

2562
02:28:36,480 --> 02:28:37,980
你认为奥本海默博士
Would you say that Dr. Oppenheimer

2563
02:28:37,980 --> 02:28:40,480
坚决反对氢弹么
was unalterably opposed to the H-bomb?

2564
02:28:40,490 --> 02:28:43,360
不  他认为开启氢弹这种核聚变项目
No, he, he thought that a fusion program

2565
02:28:43,360 --> 02:28:46,320
要以停止正在顺利进行的核裂变项目为代价
would come at the expense of our awfully good fission program.

2566
02:28:46,320 --> 02:28:48,320
但事实并非如此
But that proved not to be the case.

2567
02:28:48,490 --> 02:28:50,280
事实上  二者可以共存
In the event, both could be done.

2568
02:28:50,410 --> 02:28:52,950
假设本委员会
Suppose that this board did not feel satisfied

2569
02:28:52,960 --> 02:28:54,200
最终无法认定
that in his testimony here

2570
02:28:54,210 --> 02:28:57,240
奥本海默博士是诚实可信的
Dr. Oppenheimer had been wholly truthful,

2571
02:28:57,330 --> 02:28:59,500
你对他的清白与否持何观点呢
what would you say whether or not he should be cleared?

2572
02:28:59,500 --> 02:29:01,800
一个完成了奥本海默这般成就的人
Why go through all this against a man

2573
02:29:01,800 --> 02:29:03,840
我们为什么还要如此对待他
who has accomplished what Dr. Oppenheimer has?

2574
02:29:03,840 --> 02:29:05,330
看看他的履历
Look at his record.

2575
02:29:05,680 --> 02:29:08,010
我们拥有了原子弹  一系列原子弹
We have an A-bomb, and a whole series of it.

2576
02:29:08,010 --> 02:29:09,590
一系列氢弹
We have a whole series of super bombs.

2577
02:29:09,590 --> 02:29:10,960
你们还苛求什么
What more do you want?

2578
02:29:11,520 --> 02:29:12,550
来条美人鱼
Mermaids?

2579
02:29:13,180 --> 02:29:16,350
我和施特劳斯部长相识多年
But I've known Secretary Strauss for many years.

2580
02:29:16,350 --> 02:29:19,890
我认为有必要提及
And I feel it a necessity to express the warm support

2581
02:29:20,110 --> 02:29:22,650
路易斯对科学和科学家的暖心支持
for science and scientists Lewis has shown.

2582
02:29:22,650 --> 02:29:25,530
没什么急事的话我们先午休吧
We'll break now. Unless there's any immediate business.

2583
02:29:25,530 --> 02:29:28,620
议员先生  我想再次提请
Senator, I'd like to once again request

2584
02:29:28,660 --> 02:29:31,330
一份证人名单
that we're furnished with a list of witnesses.

