法律范围内允许的审讯技巧
all the tricks of a rather ingenious legal background.

2748
02:37:56,340 --> 02:38:00,760
你在指控格雷委员会进行的是一场检控
You are charging now that the Gray Board permitted a prosecution.

2749
02:38:01,220 --> 02:38:02,680
如果我是格雷委员会的一员
If I were on the Gray Board,

2750
02:38:03,340 --> 02:38:05,340
我会对实际作为检方的人
I would have protested against the tactics

2751
02:38:05,350 --> 02:38:08,310
使用的手段提出异议
of the man who served in fact as the prosecuting counsel.

2752
02:38:08,310 --> 02:38:10,270
他并不是委员会指派的人
A man appointed not by the Board,

2753
02:38:11,440 --> 02:38:13,310
而是路易斯·施特劳斯指派的
but by Lewis Strauss.

2754
02:38:15,480 --> 02:38:16,520
他是谁
Who was this?

2755
02:38:18,110 --> 02:38:18,940
不好意思
I'm sorry?

2756
02:38:19,820 --> 02:38:20,860
他是谁
Who was this?

2757
02:38:21,400 --> 02:38:22,570
罗杰·罗伯
Roger Robb.

2758
02:38:22,990 --> 02:38:24,450
奥本海默夫人
Mrs. Oppenheimer.

2759
02:38:28,990 --> 02:38:31,330
你有没有共产党员卡片
Did you have a Communist Party membership card?

2760
02:38:32,920 --> 02:38:35,170
我...我不确定
I'm... I'm not sure.

2761
02:38:35,170 --> 02:38:36,130
不确定
Not sure?

2762
02:38:53,640 --> 02:38:56,560
入党的途径想必是需要寄一些钱过去
I mean, presumably, the act of joining the party

2763
02:38:56,560 --> 02:38:59,770
然后收到一张卡片  没错吧
required sending some money and receiving a card, no?

2764
02:39:10,040 --> 02:39:10,990
对不起
Sorry.

2765
02:39:12,000 --> 02:39:13,040
没错
Yes.

2766
02:39:15,460 --> 02:39:18,960
只是这件事过去太久太久了  不是吗  罗伯先生
It's just, it was all so very long ago, Mr. Robb, wasn't it?

2767
02:39:18,960 --> 02:39:20,340
-也不是吧  -久到让人忘记了
- Not really. - Long enough to have forgotten.

2768
02:39:20,340 --> 02:39:22,090
你把卡片还回去了吗  还是撕掉了
Did you return the card, or rip it up?

2769
02:39:22,090 --> 02:39:23,670
你说的是我都不记得有过的那张卡片吗
The card whose existence I've forgotten?

2770
02:39:23,670 --> 02:39:26,840
-你的共产党员卡吗  -没有一点印象
- Your Communist Party membership card? - Haven't the slightest idea.

2771
02:39:29,850 --> 02:39:34,180
你能区分苏联共产主义和共产主义吗
Can a distinction be made between Soviet communism and communism?

2772
02:39:34,350 --> 02:39:35,560
在我还是党员时
In the days when I was a member,

2773
02:39:35,560 --> 02:39:37,650
我认为二者是完全不同的
I thought they were definitely two things.

2774
02:39:37,650 --> 02:39:40,270
我认为美国共产党
I thought that the Communist Party of the United States

2775
02:39:40,270 --> 02:39:42,480
关心的是国内的问题
was concerned with our domestic problems.

2776
02:39:42,480 --> 02:39:44,110
我现在不相信这点了
I now no longer believe this.

2777
02:39:44,110 --> 02:39:45,280
我认为一切都联系了起来
I believe the whole thing's linked together

2778
02:39:45,280 --> 02:39:46,570
向全世界扩散开去
and spread all over the world,

2779
02:39:46,570 --> 02:39:50,700
我16年前退党以后  一直坚信这一点
and I have believed this since I left the party 16 years ago.

2780
02:39:50,700 --> 02:39:53,580
-但是...  -17年前  我记错了
- But... - 17 years ago. My mistake.

2781
02:39:53,620 --> 02:39:55,370
-但你...  -抱歉  是18
- But you... - Sorry, 18.

2782
02:39:56,460 --> 02:39:58,000
18年前
18 years ago.

2783
02:39:59,130 --> 02:40:01,670
你是否清楚你的丈夫直到1942年
Are you familiar with the fact your husband was making contributions

2784
02:40:01,670 --> 02:40:04,420
都还在为西班牙内战出力
to the Spanish Civil War as late as 1942?

2785
02:40:04,420 --> 02:40:06,590
我知道罗伯特会时不时往外汇款
I knew that Robert gave money from time to time.

2786
02:40:06,590 --> 02:40:09,300
你知道这些钱会流入共产党的渠道吗
Did you know this money was going into Communist Party channels?

2787
02:40:09,300 --> 02:40:11,390
-你是说经过吗  -你说什么
- Don't you mean through? - Pardon?

2788
02:40:11,390 --> 02:40:14,560
你应该是想说钱会经过共产党的渠道  对吧
I think you mean through Communist Party channels, don't you?

2789
02:40:14,560 --> 02:40:15,640
-对  -是吗
- Yes. - Yes?

2790
02:40:15,640 --> 02:40:17,560
-是的  -好的
- Yes. - Yes.

2791
02:40:17,560 --> 02:40:20,810
那这是否意味着直至1942年
Then would it be fair to say that this meant that by 1942,

2792
02:40:20,810 --> 02:40:21,900
你的丈夫还没有停止
your husband had not stopped

2793
02:40:21,900 --> 02:40:23,980
与共产党的瓜葛呢
having anything to do with the Communist Party?

2794
02:40:25,110 --> 02:40:26,360
你不用只回答是或否
You don't have to answer that yes or no,

2795
02:40:26,360 --> 02:40:27,820
你可以按照你的想法回答
you can answer that any way you wish.

2796
02:40:27,820 --> 02:40:30,910
我知道  谢谢  你的提问有问题
I know that, thank you. It's your question.

2797
02:40:31,660 --> 02:40:33,030
表述得不太到位
It's not properly phrased.

2798
02:40:33,040 --> 02:40:34,660
-你知道我想问什么吗  -我知道
- Do you understand what I'm getting at? - I do.

2799
02:40:34,660 --> 02:40:35,450
那为什么不按照那个来回答呢
Then why don't you answer it that way?

2800
02:40:35,450 --> 02:40:37,500
因为我不喜欢你的措辞
Because I don't like your phrase,

2801
02:40:37,660 --> 02:40:39,540
"与共产党的瓜葛"
"having anything to do with the Communist Party,"

2802
02:40:39,540 --> 02:40:41,080
因为罗伯特和共产党
because Robert never had anything to do

2803
02:40:41,080 --> 02:40:42,920
从来没有任何关系
with the Communist Party as such.

2804
02:40:42,920 --> 02:40:45,300
我知道他给西班牙难民捐款
I know he gave money to Spanish refugees.

2805
02:40:45,300 --> 02:40:48,550
我知道他对共产主义思想很感兴趣
I know he took an intellectual interest in communist ideas.

2806
02:40:48,550 --> 02:40:50,430
有两种共产主义者吗
Are there two types of communists?

2807
02:40:50,430 --> 02:40:53,300
思想共产主义者  以及你们普通的共产主义者
Intellectual communists, and your plain old regular commie?

2808
02:40:54,510 --> 02:40:56,220
我回答不了这个问题
I couldn't answer that one.

2809
02:40:57,230 --> 02:40:58,480
我也不能
I couldn't either.

2810
02:41:05,610 --> 02:41:06,610
晚安
Good evening.

2811
02:41:06,900 --> 02:41:08,320
罗伯特  你赢不了
Robert, you can't win this thing.

2812
02:41:08,320 --> 02:41:10,700
这是一个有着预定结果的袋鼠法庭[无视公平正义和司法程序]It's a kangaroo court with a predetermined outcome.

2813
02:41:10,700 --> 02:41:12,490
为什么还要让自己经历这些呢
Why put yourself through more of it?

2814
02:41:13,160 --> 02:41:14,780
我有我的原因
I have my reasons.

2815
02:41:16,200 --> 02:41:16,950
好吧
Alright.

2816
02:41:17,700 --> 02:41:18,540
晚安
Good night.

2817
02:41:23,250 --> 02:41:24,880
他说得有道理
He has a point.

2818
02:41:25,960 --> 02:41:28,630
-我觉得你不理解  阿尔伯特  -是吗
- I'm not sure you understand, Albert. - No?

2819
02:41:29,630 --> 02:41:32,180
我离开了我的祖国  再没回去
I left my country, never to return.

2820
02:41:33,140 --> 02:41:34,970
你对你的祖国尽职尽责
You served your country well.

2821
02:41:35,510 --> 02:41:38,100
如果这就是她给你的回报...
If this is the reward she offers you, then...

2822
02:41:39,100 --> 02:41:41,520
或许你应该考虑放弃她
perhaps you should turn your back on her.

2823
02:41:42,520 --> 02:41:44,560
不巧  我非常热爱这个国家
Damn it, I happen to love this country.

2824
02:41:45,270 --> 02:41:47,320
那就让他们见鬼去吧
Then tell them to go to hell.

2825
02:41:47,860 --> 02:41:51,650
好了  再也没有什么确认听证会
Interestingly enough, this is no longer a confirmation hearing.

2826
02:41:51,660 --> 02:41:53,110
现在  这就是审判
It's now a trial...

2827
02:41:53,700 --> 02:41:54,990
关于一场审判的审判
about a trial!

2828
02:41:54,990 --> 02:41:56,450
我的老天啊
For god's sakes!

2829
02:41:56,540 --> 02:41:59,250
情况不太妙  他告诉大家是你发起的听证会
It's not good he's telling everyone you initiated the hearings.

2830
02:41:59,250 --> 02:42:01,330
他什么都没法证明
He can't prove a goddamn thing.

2831
02:42:01,330 --> 02:42:04,920
他绝对无法证明是我把文件给了波登
He certainly can't prove that I gave the file to Borden.

2832
02:42:04,920 --> 02:42:07,960
我们不是在法庭  先生  无需举证
We're not in court, sir. There's no burden of proof.

2833
02:42:08,170 --> 02:42:09,960
没错  他们不是来定罪的
Right, they're not convicting.

2834
02:42:10,920 --> 02:42:12,380
是要搞垮我
They're just denying.

2835
02:42:12,800 --> 02:42:15,680
希尔为什么会来诋毁我  他是出于什么目的
Why would Hill come here to tear me down? What's his angle?

2836
02:42:15,680 --> 02:42:17,970
见义当为需要理由吗
Do people need a reason to do the right thing?

2837
02:42:18,270 --> 02:42:20,470
-在他看来  -我告诉过你
- As he sees it. - I told you.

2838
02:42:20,480 --> 02:42:22,940
从第一次见面起  奥本海默就一直怂恿
Oppenheimer's been poisoning the scientists against me

2839
02:42:22,940 --> 02:42:24,650
科学家们跟我对着干
right from that first meeting.

2840
02:42:24,650 --> 02:42:27,400
我不知道那天奥本海默对他说了什么
I don't know what Oppenheimer said to him that day,

2841
02:42:27,400 --> 02:42:30,610
但爱因斯坦甚至都不愿拿正眼看我
but Einstein wouldn't even meet my eye.

2842
02:42:32,150 --> 02:42:34,360
奥本海默很擅长操纵同僚
Oppenheimer knows how to manipulate his own.

2843
02:42:34,570 --> 02:42:36,030
在洛斯阿拉莫斯
At Los Alamos,

2844
02:42:36,240 --> 02:42:38,530
他就利用过那些科学家的天真
he preyed on the naivete of scientists

2845
02:42:38,540 --> 02:42:41,080
他们以为有权决定我们如何使用其研究成果
who thought they get a say in how we use their work.

2846
02:42:41,080 --> 02:42:43,540
他们绝对想不到  他本人其实那样幼稚无知
They'll never think he was that naive himself.

2847
02:42:43,830 --> 02:42:47,330
博士  在氢弹研究的过程中
Doctor, during your work on the hydrogen bomb,

2848
02:42:47,340 --> 02:42:50,260
你是否曾因道义上的不安而止步不前
were you... deterred by any moral qualms?

2849
02:42:50,960 --> 02:42:52,090
是的  当然
Yes, of course.

2850
02:42:52,340 --> 02:42:54,130
但你还是继续研究下去了  对不对
But you still got on with your work, didn't you?

2851
02:42:54,130 --> 02:42:56,050
对  因为我做的是科学探索
Yes, because this was work of exploration,

2852
02:42:56,050 --> 02:42:58,550
不是武器研制
it was not the preparation of a weapon.

2853
02:42:58,560 --> 02:43:00,560
你是说这更像种学术涉猎
You mean it was more of an academic excursion?

2854
02:43:00,560 --> 02:43:02,220
不  如果能造出氢弹
No, it is not an academic thing,

2855
02:43:02,230 --> 02:43:03,810
就不是学术了
whether you can build a hydrogen bomb.

2856
02:43:03,810 --> 02:43:05,100
而是生死攸关的大事
It's a matter of life and death.

2857
02:43:05,100 --> 02:43:06,940
你在1942年
By 1942, you were actively pushing

2858
02:43:06,940 --> 02:43:08,480
曾积极推动氢弹研制  不是吗
the development of the hydrogen bomb, weren't you?

2859
02:43:08,480 --> 02:43:09,940
"推动"这个词不恰当
Pushing is not the right word.

2860
02:43:09,940 --> 02:43:11,820
是支持并参与研究
Supporting it and working on it, yes.

2861
02:43:11,820 --> 02:43:14,110
那这种道义上的不安是何时变得如此强烈
So when did these moral qualms become so strong

2862
02:43:14,110 --> 02:43:17,490
强到让你积极反对氢弹研制
that you actively opposed the development of the hydrogen bomb?

2863
02:43:17,490 --> 02:43:20,080
当有人说美国的政策是
When it was suggested that it be the policy of the United States

2864
02:43:20,080 --> 02:43:21,790
不惜一切代价制造出这些武器
to make these things at all costs,

2865
02:43:21,790 --> 02:43:24,330
而不考虑这些武器
without regard to the balance between these weapons

2866
02:43:24,330 --> 02:43:26,830
和我们的武器库中已有的核武器之间的平衡
and atomic weapons as part of our arsenal.

2867
02:43:28,340 --> 02:43:30,500
这与道义上的不安有什么关系
What do moral qualms have to do with that?

2868
02:43:31,760 --> 02:43:33,760
-与道义上的不安有什么关系  -对
- What do moral qualms have to do with it? - Yes.

2869
02:43:33,760 --> 02:43:36,010
奥本海默想独占原子弹
Oppenheimer wanted to own the atomic bomb.

2870
02:43:36,010 --> 02:43:38,010
他想成为撼动地球之人
He wanted to be The Man Who Moved the Earth.

2871
02:43:38,010 --> 02:43:42,520
他现在说要把"核妖魔"关回瓶中
He talks about putting the nuclear genie back in the bottle.

2872
02:43:42,520 --> 02:43:44,770
告诉你吧  我非常清楚
Well, I'm here to tell you that I know,

2873
02:43:45,020 --> 02:43:47,940
如果能重头来过  J·罗伯特·奥本海默
J. Robert Oppenheimer, if he could do it all over,

2874
02:43:47,940 --> 02:43:49,560
还是会做出相同选择
he'd do it all the same.

2875
02:43:49,560 --> 02:43:53,230
知道吗  他从未说过对轰炸广岛感到后悔
You know he's never once said that he regrets Hiroshima?

2876
02:43:53,240 --> 02:43:55,570
他还是会这么做  为什么
He'd do it all over. Why?

2877
02:43:55,860 --> 02:44:00,490
因为这让他成为有史以来最重要的人
Because it made him the most important man who ever lived.

2878
02:44:01,160 --> 02:44:03,790
我们不加限制地使用原子弹
We freely used the atomic bomb.

2879
02:44:03,790 --> 02:44:05,910
博士  事实上你协助选择了
In fact, Doctor, you assisted in selecting the target

2880
02:44:05,910 --> 02:44:08,290
在日本投放原子弹的目标  不是吗
to drop the atomic bomb on Japan, didn't you?

2881
02:44:08,750 --> 02:44:10,040
-对...  -那你知道  对吧
- Yes... - Well then, you knew, did you not,

2882
02:44:10,040 --> 02:44:12,550
向你选择的目标投放原子弹
that by dropping that atomic bomb on the target you selected,

2883
02:44:12,550 --> 02:44:14,670
会有成千上万的平民伤亡
that thousands of civilians would be killed or injured.

2884
02:44:14,670 --> 02:44:15,760
对吗
Is that correct?

2885
02:44:16,090 --> 02:44:17,840
对  我没想到会有那么多
Yes, not as many as turned out.

2886
02:44:17,840 --> 02:44:20,550
那有多少人伤亡
Oh. Then how many were killed or injured?

2887
02:44:20,850 --> 02:44:23,260
-七万人  -七万人  广岛和...
- 70,000. - 70,000, both Hiroshima and...

2888
02:44:23,270 --> 02:44:26,480
-总计十一万人  -轰炸当天的伤亡人数吗
- 110,000 to both. - On the day of each bombing?

2889
02:44:28,060 --> 02:44:28,890
对
Yes.

2890
02:44:28,900 --> 02:44:30,350
轰炸数周及数年以后呢
And in the weeks and years that followed?

2891
02:44:30,360 --> 02:44:33,520
估计有五至十万人
It has been put at somewhere between 50,000 and 100,000.

2892
02:44:33,530 --> 02:44:35,230
至少有二十二万人死亡
220,000 dead, at least.

2893
02:44:35,240 --> 02:44:37,450
-是的  -对此你会良心有愧吗
- Yes. - Any moral scruples about that?

2894
02:44:39,410 --> 02:44:40,280
备受煎熬
Terrible ones.

2895
02:44:40,280 --> 02:44:41,570
但你却在这里言之凿凿
But yet you testified in here

2896
02:44:41,580 --> 02:44:44,330
说轰炸广岛非常成功
that the bombing of Hiroshima was very successful.

2897
02:44:44,410 --> 02:44:47,330
-技术上很成功  -技术上非常成功
- Technically successful. - Oh! Technically it was very successful.

2898
02:44:47,330 --> 02:44:49,750
据说这加速了战争的结束
And it is also alleged to have helped to end the war.

2899
02:44:49,750 --> 02:44:50,460
你会支持
Would you have been supportive

2900
02:44:50,460 --> 02:44:53,090
向广岛投放氢弹吗
of the dropping of a hydrogen bomb on Hiroshima?

2901
02:44:53,090 --> 02:44:54,670
这根本没有意义
That would make no sense at all.

2902
02:44:54,670 --> 02:44:57,300
-为什么  -目标太小
- Why? - The target is too small.

2903
02:44:57,300 --> 02:44:59,430
假设日本有足够大的
Well, supposing there had been a target in Japan

2904
02:44:59,430 --> 02:45:01,180
可以投放热核武器的目标
big enough for a thermonuclear weapon,

2905
02:45:01,180 --> 02:45:02,680
你会反对投放吗
would you have been opposed to the dropping of it?

2906
02:45:02,680 --> 02:45:04,640
我当时没遇到这样的问题
This was not a problem with which I was confronted.

2907
02:45:04,640 --> 02:45:06,430
那我现在问你  先生
Well, I'm confronting you with it now, sir.

2908
02:45:06,430 --> 02:45:07,930
这都是他计划的一部分
It was all part of his plan.

2909
02:45:07,930 --> 02:45:11,900
他想要那种荣耀  自大  不真诚的负罪感
He wanted the glorious, insincere guilt of the self-important

2910
02:45:11,900 --> 02:45:14,360
像王冠一样戴在头上  并说
to wear like a fucking crown and say,

2911
02:45:14,360 --> 02:45:16,860
"不  我们不能走上这条路"
"No, we cannot go down this road,"

2912
02:45:16,860 --> 02:45:19,650
即使他知道我们不得不这样做
even as he knew we'd have to.

2913
02:45:19,650 --> 02:45:21,160
你会因为道德顾虑
Would you have been opposed to the dropping

2914
