反对向日本投放热核武器吗
of a thermonuclear weapon on Japan because of moral scruples?

2915
02:45:23,870 --> 02:45:25,240
是的  我想我会  先生
Yes, I believe I would, sir.

2916
02:45:25,240 --> 02:45:27,490
你反对向广岛投放原子弹
Did you oppose the dropping of an atomic bomb on Hiroshima

2917
02:45:27,500 --> 02:45:28,790
是因为道德顾虑吗
because of moral scruples?

2918
02:45:28,790 --> 02:45:31,210
-我们阐述了我们的...  -不  你你你你
- We set forth our... - No, you, you, you, you!

2919
02:45:31,210 --> 02:45:32,210
-我问的是你...  -我阐...
- I'm asking you... - I set...

2920
02:45:32,210 --> 02:45:34,590
-你你你  -我阐述了我们
- You, you, you! - I set forth our arguments

2921
02:45:34,590 --> 02:45:36,880
反对投放的理由  但我并不支持不投
against dropping it, but I did not endorse them.

2922
02:45:36,880 --> 02:45:38,380
你是说日以继夜工作三年
You mean after working night and day

2923
02:45:38,380 --> 02:45:40,130
造出原子弹后
for three years building the bomb,

2924
02:45:40,130 --> 02:45:42,340
你却反对使用它
you then argued against the use of it?

2925
02:45:42,430 --> 02:45:44,640
战争部长当时询问我
I was asked by the Secretary of War

2926
02:45:44,640 --> 02:45:46,010
科学家们的看法
what the views of scientists were.

2927
02:45:46,010 --> 02:45:48,600
我告诉了他们反对和赞成的意见
I gave them the views against and the views for.

2928
02:45:48,600 --> 02:45:50,560
你赞成向日本投放
You supported the dropping of the atom bomb

2929
02:45:50,560 --> 02:45:51,640
-原子弹  对吗  -你什么意思...
- on Japan, didn't you? - What do you mean...

2930
02:45:51,650 --> 02:45:53,440
-你赞成...  -你说"赞成"是什么意思
- You supported it... - What do you mean, support?

2931
02:45:53,440 --> 02:45:54,940
你帮助选择了目标  不是吗
Well, you helped pick the target, didn't you?

2932
02:45:54,940 --> 02:45:58,610
我是公事公办  我在洛斯阿拉莫斯没有决策权
I did my job. I was not in a policy-making position at Los Alamos.

2933
02:45:58,610 --> 02:46:00,570
命令我做什么我就做什么
I would have done anything I was asked to do.

2934
02:46:00,570 --> 02:46:02,990
那你本来也该造出氢弹的  不是吗
Well, then, you would have built the H-bomb too, wouldn't you?

2935
02:46:02,990 --> 02:46:05,450
-但我没法...  -我没问你这个  博士
- But I couldn't... - I didn't ask you that, Doctor!

2936
02:46:05,450 --> 02:46:07,830
苏联核试验后  你与人合署的
And the GAC report, which you co-authored

2937
02:46:07,830 --> 02:46:09,870
总顾问委员会报告上写道
after the Soviet atomic test said:

2938
02:46:09,870 --> 02:46:12,830
"永远不该造出氢弹"
"A super bomb should never be built!"

2939
02:46:12,830 --> 02:46:14,380
我们的意思是  我的意思是...
What we meant, what I meant...

2940
02:46:14,380 --> 02:46:15,710
-"我们"是谁  -听着  我的意思是...
- What you, who? - Look, what I meant...

2941
02:46:15,710 --> 02:46:16,500
谁
Who?

2942
02:46:18,050 --> 02:46:21,090
苏联人难道不会尽全力增强自己的军事实力吗
Well, wouldn't the Russians do anything to increase their strength?

2943
02:46:21,680 --> 02:46:23,550
如果我们造出来了  他们就必须造出来
If we did it, they would have to do it!

2944
02:46:23,550 --> 02:46:25,720
我们的努力只会让他们更努力
Our efforts would only fuel their efforts,

2945
02:46:25,720 --> 02:46:27,970
就像原子弹那样
just as it had with the atomic bomb!

2946
02:46:27,970 --> 02:46:30,640
没错  就像原子弹那样
Just as it had with the atomic bomb, exactly!

2947
02:46:31,770 --> 02:46:36,060
1945年毫无道德顾虑  1949年顾虑重重
No moral scruples in 1945, plenty in 1949.

2948
02:46:40,240 --> 02:46:41,650
奥本海默博士...
Dr. Oppenheimer...

2949
02:46:43,660 --> 02:46:46,320
你对氢弹强烈的道德感
when did your strong moral convictions develop

2950
02:46:46,320 --> 02:46:48,490
是什么时候形成的
with respect to the hydrogen bomb?

2951
02:46:56,130 --> 02:46:57,790
当我明白
When it became clear to me

2952
02:46:59,250 --> 02:47:02,510
我们会动用手中的任何武器时
that we would tend to use any weapon we had.

2953
02:47:05,470 --> 02:47:07,640
殉道者J·罗伯特·奥本海默
J. Robert Oppenheimer the martyr,

2954
02:47:07,640 --> 02:47:10,520
我正好满足了他的心愿
I gave him exactly what he wanted.

2955
02:47:10,970 --> 02:47:12,680
因"三位一体"而被世人铭记
To be remembered for Trinity,

2956
02:47:12,680 --> 02:47:14,690
不是因为广岛
not Hiroshima!

2957
02:47:15,310 --> 02:47:17,480
也不是因为长崎
Not Nagasaki!

2958
02:47:20,400 --> 02:47:22,280
他应该感谢我
He should be thanking me.

2959
02:47:23,240 --> 02:47:24,450
他并不
Well, he's not.

2960
02:47:27,870 --> 02:47:29,410
我们的票数还够吗
Do we still have enough votes?

2961
02:47:29,410 --> 02:47:31,290
还是我职业生涯的巅峰时刻
Or is the crowning moment of my career

2962
02:47:31,290 --> 02:47:34,710
即将成为我人生中最大的公开羞辱
about to become the most public humiliation of my life?

2963
02:47:35,250 --> 02:47:37,250
参议院全体议员即将投票
Full Senate's about to vote.

2964
02:47:37,960 --> 02:47:39,080
你会勉强通过
You'll scrape through.

2965
02:47:39,090 --> 02:47:40,840
很好  那召集媒体吧
Great, then gather the fucking press.

2966
02:47:40,840 --> 02:47:42,710
J·罗伯特·奥本海默博士
Dr. J. Robert Oppenheimer,

2967
02:47:42,760 --> 02:47:45,630
本委员会听取了你
this board, having heard testimony from you

2968
02:47:45,630 --> 02:47:49,050
及你的许多前同事和现同事的证词
and many of your current and former colleagues,

2969
02:47:49,100 --> 02:47:53,270
我们得出一致结论  你是个忠诚的公民
has come to the unanimous conclusion that you are a loyal citizen.

2970
02:47:55,520 --> 02:47:56,440
然而...
However...

2971
02:47:57,400 --> 02:48:00,610
鉴于你一直与共党分子牵扯不清
In the light of your continuing associations,

2972
02:48:00,610 --> 02:48:04,240
以及你对本国安全机构的漠视
and disregard for the security apparatus of this country,

2973
02:48:04,320 --> 02:48:07,780
外加你在氢弹项目上
together with your somewhat disturbing conduct

2974
02:48:07,780 --> 02:48:09,660
令人不安的行为
on the hydrogen bomb program,

2975
02:48:10,080 --> 02:48:11,330
并且很遗憾  你对本委员会的
and the regrettable lack of candor

2976
02:48:11,330 --> 02:48:13,950
一些回应缺乏坦诚
in certain of your responses to this board,

2977
02:48:14,580 --> 02:48:16,540
经过投票  2比1
we have voted, two-to-one,

2978
02:48:17,420 --> 02:48:20,580
我们拒绝延长你的安全许可
to deny the renewal of your security clearance.

2979
02:48:20,590 --> 02:48:23,960
完整的书面意见  包括埃文斯先生的异议
A full written opinion, with a dissent from Mr. Evans,

2980
02:48:24,130 --> 02:48:27,090
几天后将呈交原子能委员会
will be issued to the AEC in the coming days.

2981
02:48:27,220 --> 02:48:28,090
会议结束
That is all.

2982
02:48:39,230 --> 02:48:42,190
罗伯特  罗伯特
Robert. Robert.

2983
02:48:45,490 --> 02:48:46,780
别...
Don't...

2984
02:48:49,300 --> 02:48:50,950
别收床单
Don't take in the sheets.

2985
02:48:56,700 --> 02:48:58,830
两分钟  就两分钟
Two minutes. Two minutes!

2986
02:48:59,000 --> 02:49:00,460
会让你们拍的
You'll get your shot!

2987
02:49:04,050 --> 02:49:05,760
正式宣布了吗
Is it official?

2988
02:49:07,510 --> 02:49:11,430
有几个意料之外的反对者
Well, there were a couple of unexpected holdouts.

2989
02:49:16,470 --> 02:49:18,770
我被否决了  对吗
I'm denied. Yeah?

2990
02:49:19,310 --> 02:49:21,100
-恐怕是的  先生  -好吧
- I'm afraid so, sir. - Alright.

2991
02:49:28,740 --> 02:49:29,990
反对者有谁
Who were the holdouts?

2992
02:49:29,990 --> 02:49:32,870
有三位
Um, there were three.

2993
02:49:32,870 --> 02:49:35,410
以马萨诸塞州的新晋参议员为首
Led by the junior senator from Massachusetts.

2994
02:49:35,410 --> 02:49:36,990
一个想出名的年轻人
Young guy trying to make a name for himself,

2995
02:49:37,000 --> 02:49:39,290
不喜欢你对奥本海默所做的事
didn't like what you did to Oppenheimer.

2996
02:49:39,910 --> 02:49:40,960
他叫什么
What's his name?

2997
02:49:41,620 --> 02:49:43,460
肯尼迪
Uh, Kennedy.

2998
02:49:43,670 --> 02:49:44,960
约翰·F·肯尼迪
John F. Kennedy.

2999
02:49:48,680 --> 02:49:49,590
吉蒂
Kitty?

3000
02:49:56,140 --> 02:49:59,890
你以为任由他们肆意凌虐你
Did you think that if you let them tar and feather you,

3001
02:49:59,890 --> 02:50:01,770
全世界就会原谅你吗
then the world would forgive you?

3002
02:50:05,560 --> 02:50:06,770
不会的
It won't.

3003
02:50:09,280 --> 02:50:10,320
我们走着瞧
We'll see.

3004
02:50:25,040 --> 02:50:26,790
你说我会没事的
You told me I'd be okay.

3005
02:50:27,340 --> 02:50:29,380
对  但你没把所有事告诉我  对吗
Yeah, well, I didn't have all the facts, did I?

3006
02:50:29,380 --> 02:50:30,630
事实上
Here's a fact.

3007
02:50:30,630 --> 02:50:32,800
艾森豪威尔总统去年亲手在我胸前
President Eisenhower pinned the Medal of Freedom

3008
02:50:32,800 --> 02:50:34,720
别上自由勋章
on my chest last year,

3009
02:50:34,720 --> 02:50:37,100
因为我做的都是利国利民的事
because I've always done what's right for this country.

3010
02:50:37,100 --> 02:50:41,310
他们不希望我进入内阁  没...  没关系
They don't want me in the cabinet room? Well, that's... that's fine.

3011
02:50:41,890 --> 02:50:44,230
也许他们应该转而邀请奥本海默
Maybe they should just invite Oppenheimer instead.

3012
02:50:44,230 --> 02:50:45,400
也许他们会的
Maybe they will.

3013
02:50:46,230 --> 02:50:49,320
我告诉过你  他唆使那些科学家反对我
I told you. He turned the scientists against me,

3014
02:50:49,320 --> 02:50:51,240
从爱因斯坦开始  一个接着一个
one by one, starting with Einstein.

3015
02:50:51,240 --> 02:50:53,900
我跟你说过  爱因斯坦  爱因斯坦在池塘边
I told you about that. Einstein. Einstein by the pond.

3016
02:50:53,910 --> 02:50:56,620
是的  但先生  既然没人...
You did, but you know, sir, since nobody...

3017
02:50:57,030 --> 02:50:59,200
真正知道他们那天到底聊了什么
really knows what they said to each other that day,

3018
02:50:59,200 --> 02:51:02,750
有没有可能他们根本没说起你
is it possible they didn't talk about you at all?

3019
02:51:03,060 --> 02:51:05,420
有没有可能他们聊的是...
Is it possible they spoke about something, uh...

3020
02:51:06,380 --> 02:51:07,500
更重要的事
more important?

3021
02:51:07,500 --> 02:51:11,340
施特劳斯先生  看这里  施特劳斯先生
Mr. Strauss. Over here! Mr. Strauss!

3022
02:51:22,610 --> 02:51:23,730
谢谢
Thank you.

3023
02:51:24,010 --> 02:51:25,140
阿尔伯特
Albert.

3024
02:51:28,610 --> 02:51:30,320
当下风云人物
The man of the moment.

3025
02:51:34,280 --> 02:51:38,490
你曾在伯克利为我办过一场招待会
You once held a reception for me in Berkeley.

3026
02:51:38,490 --> 02:51:40,990
-你给我颁了奖  -是的
- You gave me an award, hmm? - Yes.

3027
02:51:42,040 --> 02:51:44,540
你们都以为我已无法理解
You all thought that I had lost the ability

3028
02:51:44,540 --> 02:51:46,920
我所开创的领域
to understand what I'd started.

3029
02:51:47,500 --> 02:51:48,290
所以...
So...

3030
02:51:48,840 --> 02:51:53,090
那个奖不是颁给我的  是给你们的  对吗
The award really wasn't for me, it was for all of you, hmm?

3031
02:51:55,130 --> 02:51:56,510
现在轮到你
Now it's your turn

3032
02:51:57,340 --> 02:52:01,850
来解决自己的成就带来的问题
to deal with the consequences of your achievement.

3033
02:52:02,890 --> 02:52:06,520
终有一天  等他们对你惩罚够了
And one day, when they've punished you enough,

3034
02:52:08,520 --> 02:52:12,360
就会给你奉上三文鱼和土豆沙拉
they'll serve you salmon and potato salad.

3035
02:52:16,450 --> 02:52:17,990
演讲称颂你
Make speeches.

3036
02:52:19,180 --> 02:52:20,620
给你颁奖
Give you a medal.

3037
02:52:22,740 --> 02:52:24,120
你好  弗兰克
Hello, Frank.

3038
02:52:24,700 --> 02:52:26,210
你幸福  我就幸福
You're happy, I'm happy.

3039
02:52:32,800 --> 02:52:35,630
拍着你的背告诉你  一切都过去了
Pat you on the back, tell you all is forgiven.

3040
02:52:37,300 --> 02:52:38,630
记住...
Just remember...

3041
02:52:40,420 --> 02:52:42,430
那些都不是为了你
it won't be for you.

3042
02:52:47,480 --> 02:52:48,980
而是为了他们自己
It'll be for them.

3043
02:53:02,360 --> 02:53:03,370
阿尔伯特...
Albert...

3044
02:53:05,660 --> 02:53:08,620
当我带着那些计算结果去找你时
when I came to you with those calculations,

3045
02:53:08,870 --> 02:53:10,960
我们都以为我们可能会触发
we thought we might start a chain reaction

3046
02:53:10,960 --> 02:53:14,420
摧毁整个世界的链式反应
that would destroy the entire world.

3047
02:53:15,840 --> 02:53:19,180
我记得  怎么了
I remember it well. What of it?

3048
02:53:22,760 --> 02:53:24,220
我想我们触发了
I believe we did.

